{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"sourceId":"lifeSituationPacks","displayName":"Life Situation Packs","type":"quotes","language":"English","edition":"Life Situation Pack","primaryCategory":"Practical Life & Wellbeing","subcategory":"Life Situations","audienceTags":["daily-use","wellbeing"],"sortPriority":11,"itemCount":895,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true,"browseOrder":"sequence","groupingLevels":["category","source"],"groupingLabels":["Situation","Pack"],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/LifeSituationPacks.json","version":"1.0"},"data":[{"id":"life-situation-0001","text":"I keep the telephone of my mind open to peace, harmony, health, love and abundance. Then whenever doubt, anxiety, or fear try to call me, they keep getting a busy signal and soon they'll forget my number.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:0"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0002","text":"Never be in a hurry; do everything quietly and in a calm spirit. Do not lose your inner peace for anything whatsoever, even if your whole world seems upset.","author":"St. Francis de Sales","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:1"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0003","text":"Education is the proper way to promote compassion and tolerance in society. Compassion and peace of mind bring a sense of confidence that reduce stress and anxiety, whereas anger and hatred come from frustration and undermine our sense of trust. Because of ignorance, many of our problems are our own creation. Education, however, is the instrument that increases our ability to employ our own intelligence","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:2"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0004","text":"Education is the proper way to promote compassion and tolerance in society. Compassion and peace of mind bring a sense of confidence that reduce stress and anxiety, whereas anger and hatred come from frustration and undermine our sense of trust","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:3"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0005","text":"What I dream of is an art of balance, of purity and serenity devoid of troubling or depressing subject matterOea soothing, calming influence on the mind, rather like a good armchair which provides relaxation from physical fatigue.","author":"Henri Matisse","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:4"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0006","text":"Have courage for the great sorrows of life and patience for the small ones; and when you have laboriously accomplished your daily task, go to sleep in peace. God is awake.","author":"Victor Hugo","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:5"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0007","text":"We can gain no lasting peace if we approach it with suspicion and mistrust or with fear. We can gain it only if we proceed with the understanding, the confidence, and the courage which flow from conviction.","author":"Franklin D. Roosevelt","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:6"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0008","text":"Courage is the price that life exacts for granting peace. The soul that knows it not, knows no release from little things; knows not the livid loneliness of fear.","author":"Amelia Earhart","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:7"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0009","text":"Fear less, hope more; eat less, chew more; whine less, breathe more; talk less, say more; hate less, love more; and all good things are yours.","author":"Swedish proverb","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:8"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0010","text":"Peace is that state in which fear of any kind is unknown.","author":"John Buchan","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:9"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0011","text":"And when you journey in the earth, there is no blame on you if you shorten the prayer, if you fear that those who disbelieve will cause you distress, surely the unbelievers are your open enemy. (The Women 4.101)","author":"Koran","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:10"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0012","text":"The marvel of all history is the patience with which men and women submit to burdens unnecessarily laid upon them by their governments.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:11"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0013","text":"For there is no friend like a sister, in calm or stormy weather, to cheer one on the tedious way, to fetch one if one goes astray, to lift one if one totters down, to strengthen whilst one stands.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:12"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0014","text":"Quiet minds can't be perplexed or frightened, but go on in fortune or misfortune at their own private pace, like a clock during a thunderstorm.","author":"Robert Lewis Stevenson","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:13"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0015","text":"This we can all bear witness to, living as we do plagued by unremitting anxiety Oe It becomes more and more imperative that the life of the spirit be avowed as the only firm basis upon which to establish happiness and peace.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:14"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0016","text":"The life of inner peace, being harmonious and without stress, is the easiest type of existence.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:15"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0017","text":"The secret of health for both mind and body is not to mourn for the past, worry about the future, or anticipate troubles, but to live in the present moment wisely and earnestly.","author":"Buddha","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:16"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0018","text":"Peace of mind makes the body healthy, but jealousy is like a cancer. (Proverbs 14:30)","author":"The Bible","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:17"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0019","text":"Climb the mountains and get their good tidings. Nature's peace will flow into you as sunshine flows into trees. The winds will blow their own freshness into you, and the storms their energy, while cares will drop off like autumn leaves.","author":"John Muir","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:18"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0020","text":"In seasons of tumult and discord bad men have the most power; mental and moral excellence require peace and quietness.","author":"Publius Cornelius Tacitus","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:19"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0021","text":"A crust eaten in peace is better than a banquet partaken in anxiety.","author":"Aesop","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:20"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0022","text":"Better beans and bacon in peace than cakes and ale in fear.","author":"Aesop","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:21"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0023","text":"For people who like peace and quiet a phoneless cord.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:22"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0024","text":"Never continue in a job you don't enjoy. If you're happy in what you're doing, you'll like yourself, you'll have inner peace. And if you have that, along with physical health, you'll have more success than you could possibly have imagined.","author":"Roger Caras","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:23"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0025","text":"It is not a lack of real affection that scares me away again and again from marriage. Is it a fear of the comfortable life, of nice furniture, of dishonor that I burden myself with, or even the fear of becoming a contented bourgeois. ---","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:24"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0026","text":"The artistic temperament is a disease that affects amateurs. Artists of a large and wholesome vitality get rid of their art easily, as they breathe easily or perspire easily. But in artists of less force the thing becomes a pressure, and produces definite pain, which is called the artistic temperament.","author":"G. K. Chesterton","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:25"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0027","text":"I close my eyes and see the black, I open them again and I see the world, Iive hidden from fears, and that knife sears, so welcome back to the world. Donit close your eyes or you will miss the storm, and you will miss what follows after, the beauty of the rainbow.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:26"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0028","text":"When I look at ugliness, I see beauty. When I am far from home, I see old friends. When there is noise, I hear a robin's song instead. When I am in a crowd, it is the mountain's peace I feel. In the winter of my sorrow, I remember the summer of my joy. In the nighttime of my loneliness, I breathe the day of my thanksgiving. But when the sadness spreads its blanket and that is what I see, I take my eyes to some high place until I find a reflection of what lies deep inside of me.-Navajo saying","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:27"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0029","text":"Time doesn't always heal: it just breathes and swallows memories like the seasons change - sending showers; beating flowers into the mud. And nothing is forever in this place. Nothing but the way my heart fits in your hands; the held breath of hope; and the sweet lingering taste of grace.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:28"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0030","text":"Weeping willow with your tears running down, why do you always weep and frown? Is it because he left you one day? Is it because he could not stay? On your branches he would swing. Do you long for the happiness that day would bring? He found shelter in your shade. You thought his laughter would never fade. Weeping Willow, stop your tears, for there is something to calm your fears. You think death has ripped you forever apart, but I know he'll always be in your heart.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:29"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0031","text":"Maybe if I share the path I walk then a little more of your pain will vanish. I want you to heal, whoever you are. I don't care what pain you've brought the world, I just want yours to subside. No matter what, your path is yours. Dont follow misery or worry. Devote every moment of your life to improving your dreams. Love your world. Cherish the good you do. Let go of hatred. Dream of love.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:30"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0032","text":"If I could tell the world just one thing it would be we're all okay, and not to worry cause worry is wasteful and useless in times like these. I won't be made useless, only idle with despair give myself around my faith, lights the darkness most feared. My hands are small I know but they're not yours they are my own, not yours, they are my own, and I'll never be broken.","author":"Jewel Kilcher","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:31"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0033","text":"As human beings we all want to be happy and free from miseryOewe have learned that the key to happiness is inner peace. The greatest obstacles to inner peace are disturbing emotions such as anger and attachment, fear and suspicion, while love, compassion, and a sense of universal responsibility are the sources of peace and happiness.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:32"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0034","text":"As human beings we all want to be happy and free from miseryOe we have learned that the key to happiness is inner peace. The greatest obstacles to inner peace are disturbing emotions such as anger, attachment, fear and suspicion, while love and compassion and a sense of universal responsibility are the sources of peace and happiness.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:33"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0035","text":"The government has interpreted the peacefulness of the movement as a weakness: the people's non-violent policies have been taken as a green light for government violence. Refusal to resort to force has been interpreted by the government as an invitation to use armed force against the people without any fear of reprisals.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:34"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0036","text":"And once we have the condition of peace and joy in us, we can afford to be in any situation. Even in the situation of hell, we will be able to contribute our peace and serenity. The most important thing is for each of us to have some freedom in our heart, some stability in our heart, some peace in our heart. Only then will we be able to relieve the suffering around us.","author":"Thich Nhat Hahn","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:35"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0037","text":"The peace we seek to win is not victory over any other people, but the peace that comes with healing in its wings; with compassion for those who have suffered; with understanding for those who have opposed us; with the opportunity for all the peoples of this Earth to choose their own destiny.","author":"Richard M. Nixon","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:36"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0038","text":"I am convinced that some political and social activities and practices of the Catholic organizations are detrimental and even dangerous for the community as a whole, here and everywhere. I mention here only the fight against birth control at a time when overpopulation in various countries has become a serious threat to the health of people and a grave obstacle to any attempt to organize peace on this planet.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:37"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0039","text":"A desire arises in the mind. It is satisfied immediately when another comes. In the interval which separates two desires a perfect calm reigns in the mind. It is at this moment freed from all thought, love or hate. Complete peace equally reigns between two mental waves.","author":"Swami Sivananda","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:38"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0040","text":"Genius is only a greater aptitude for patience.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:39"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0041","text":"Inaction breeds doubt and fear. Action breeds confidence and courage. If you want to conquer fear, do not sit home and think about it. Go out and get busy.","author":"Dale Carnegie","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:40"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0042","text":"Government is not reason, it is not eloquence, it is force; like fire, a troublesome servant and a fearful master. Never for a moment should it be left to irresponsible action.","author":"George Washington","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:41"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0043","text":"There is no object that we see; no action that we do; no good that we enjoy; no evil that we feel, or fear, but we may make some spiritual advantage of all: and he that makes such improvement is wise, as well as pious.","author":"Anne Bradstreet","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:42"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0044","text":"We cannot seek or attain health, wealth, learning, justice or kindness in general. Action is always specific, concrete, individualized, unique.","author":"John Dewey","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:43"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0045","text":"One's action ought to come out of an achieved stillness: not to be mere rushing on.","author":"D. H. Lawrence","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:44"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0046","text":"Character isn't inherited. One builds it daily by the way one thinks and acts, thought by thought, action by action. If one lets fear or hate or anger take possession of the mind, they become self-forged chains.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:45"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0047","text":"Action conquers fear.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:46"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0048","text":"Character cannot be developed in ease and quiet. Only through experiences of trial and suffering can the soul be strengthened, vision cleared, ambition inspired and success achieved.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:47"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0049","text":"At times of great stress it is especially necessary to achieve a complete freeing of the muscles.","author":"Konstantin Stanislavsky","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:48"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0050","text":"Peace cannot be achieved through violence, it can only be attained through understanding.","author":"Ralph Waldo Emerson","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:49"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0051","text":"With firmness in the right as God gives us to see the right, let us finish the work we are in ... to do all which may achieve and cherish a just and lasting peace among ourselves.","author":"Abraham Lincoln","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:50"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0052","text":"Patience will achieve more than force.","author":"Edmund Burke","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:51"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0053","text":"One's age should be tranquil, as childhood should be playful. Hard work at either extremity of life seems out of place. At midday the sun may burn, and men labor under it; but the morning and evening should be alike calm and cheerful.","author":"Thomas Arnold","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:52"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0054","text":"As you know, no one over thirty years of age is afraid of tittle-tattle. I myself find it much less difficult to strangle a man than to fear him.","author":"Queen Christina of Sweden","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:53"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0055","text":"Nothing is inherently and invincibly young except spirit. And spirit can enter a human being perhaps better in the quiet of old age and dwell there more undisturbed than in the turmoil of adventure.","author":"George Santayana","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:54"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0056","text":"Old age has a great sense of calm and freedom.","author":"Plato","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:55"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0057","text":"It seems that fears are all based on these things: illusion and future thinking, with a side order of 'What if.' 'What if that truck turns suddenly into our lane' 'What if I'm all alone at age 80?' What if? What if? What if? Yes, fears must be respected and learned about, but they must not paralyze us, or lure us into a half-life of being afraid all the time. I liked to think of my fears being driven away in a Rolls Royce (for it is true that once you face a fear, it loses all of its stuffing, and will sit quietly in the back seat and do as it's told.) I feel that fears drive us away from our true selves--innocent beings. I used to live in denial of my fears, and try to cover them up with a 'happy face.' I now see that my greatest growth is happening with an acceptance of my fears, of giving them voices and learning new ways to deal with them.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:56"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0058","text":"Age puzzles me. I thought it was a quiet time. My seventies were interesting and fairly serene, but my eighties are passionate. I grow more intense as I age.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:57"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0059","text":"At the age of 20, we don't care what the world thinks of us; at 30, we worry about what it is thinking of us; at 40, we discover that it wasn't thinking of us at all.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:58"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0060","text":"The weather-cock on the church spire, though made of iron, would soon be broken by the storm-wind if it ... did not understand the noble art of turning to every wind.","author":"Heinrich Heine","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:59"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0061","text":"Fear no more the heat o the sun, nor the furious winter's rages. Thou thy worldly task hast done, home art gone and taken thy wages.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:60"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0062","text":"As in nature, things move violently to their place and calmly in their place, so virtue in ambition is violent, in authority settled and calm.","author":"Francis Bacon, Sr.","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:61"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0063","text":"I was bold in the pursuit of knowledge, never fearing to follow truth and reason to whatever results they led, and bearding every authority which stood in their way.","author":"Thomas Jefferson","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:62"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0064","text":"Everybody needs beauty as well as bread, places to play in and pray in, where Nature may heal and cheer and give strength to body and soul alike.","author":"John Muir","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:63"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0065","text":"Serenity and inner beauty come when we wait upon God. 'Waiting' like that is not merely wasting time.","author":"General Eva Burrows","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:64"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0066","text":"Riches, like glory or health, have no more beauty or pleasure than their possessor is pleased to lend them.","author":"Michel de Montaigne","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:65"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0067","text":"The human heart is like a ship on a stormy sea driven about by winds blowing from all four corners of heaven.","author":"Martin Luther King","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:66"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0068","text":"Thus the partial differential equation entered theoretical physics as a handmaid, but has gradually become mistress.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:67"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0069","text":"Once I knew only darkness and stillness ... my life was without past or future ... but a little word from the fingers of another fell into my hand that clutched at emptiness, and my heart leaped to the rapture of living.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:68"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0070","text":"Music is the language of the spirit. It opens the secret of life bringing peace, abolishing strife.","author":"Kahlil Gibran","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:69"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0071","text":"A musician must make music, an artist must paint, a poet must write, if he is to be ultimately at peace with himself.","author":"Abraham Maslow","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:70"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0072","text":"A wise man is superior to any insults which can be put upon him, and the best reply to unseemly behavior is patience and moderation.","author":"Moliere","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:71"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0073","text":"Peace and friendship with all mankind is our wisest policy, and I wish we may be permitted to pursue it.","author":"Thomas Jefferson","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:72"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0074","text":"A pulse in the eternal mind, no less, gives somewhere back the thoughts by England given. Her sights and sounds; dreams happy as her day; and laughter, learnt of friends; and gentleness, in hearts at peace, under an English heaven.","author":"Rupert Brooke","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:73"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0075","text":"Without peace, all other dreams vanish and are reduced to ashes.","author":"Jawaharlal Nehru","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:74"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0076","text":"Deep into that darkness peering, long I stood there, wondering, fearing, doubting, dreaming dreams no mortal ever dared to dream before.","author":"Edgar Allan Poe","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:75"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0077","text":"What difference is there between us, save a restless dream that follows my soul but fears to come near you?","author":"Kahlil Gibran","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:76"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0078","text":"Dreams permit each and every one of us to be quietly and safely insane every night of our lives.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:77"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0079","text":"Consult not your fears but your hopes and your dreams. Think not about your frustrations, but about your unfulfilled potential. Concern yourself not with what you tried and failed in, but with what it is still possible for you to do.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:78"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0080","text":"It is good to realize that if love and peace can prevail on earth, and if we can teach our children to honour nature's gifts, the joys and beauties of the outdoors will be here forever.","author":"Jimmy Carter","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:79"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0081","text":"You pray in your distress and in your need; would that you might also pray in the fullness of your joy and in your days of abundance.","author":"Kahlil Gibran","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:80"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0082","text":"Now the God of hope fill you with all joy and peace in believing, that ye may abound in hope, through the power of the Holy Ghost (Romans 15:13).","author":"The Bible","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:81"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0083","text":"If you do a good job for others, you heal yourself at the same time, because a dose of joy is a spiritual cure.","author":"Dietrich Bonhoeffer","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:82"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0084","text":"I slept under a roof my father owned, in a bed my father bought. Nothing was mine except my heart, and my fears, and my growing knowledge that not every road was gonna lead home anymore.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:83"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0085","text":"Courage is a special kind of knowledge: the knowledge of how to fear what ought to be feared and how not to fear what ought no to be feared.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:84"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0086","text":"Iim young, I live in a house my father owns, in a bed my father bought. Nothing is mine, except my hope and my fears and my growing knowledge that not every road is gonna lead home anymore.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:85"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0087","text":"Time is too slow for those who wait, too swift for those who fear, too long for those who grieve, too short for those who rejoice, but for those who love, time is eternity.","author":"Henry Van Dyke","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:86"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0088","text":"The things that will destroy America are prosperity at any price, peace at any price, safety first instead of duty first and love of soft living and the get-rich-quick theory of life.","author":"Theodore Roosevelt","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:87"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0089","text":"Love is the voice under all silences, the hope which has no opposite in fear; the strength so strong mere force is feebleness: the truth more first than sun, more last than star ...","author":"E. E. Cummings","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:88"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0090","text":"This is one of the most important moments in the life of our country. I stand here before you filled with deep pride and joy - pride in the ordinary, humble people of this country. You have shown such calm, patient determination to reclaim this country as your own, and now the joy that we can loudly proclaim from the rooftops - Free at last! Free at last! I stand before you humbled by your courage, with a heart full of love for you. I regard it as the highest honor to lead the ANC at this moment in our history. I am your servant ... . It is not the individuals that matter, but the collective ... . This is the time to heal the old wounds and build a new South Africa.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:89"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0091","text":"This is the true nature of home -- it is the place of Peace; the shelter, not only from injury, but from all terror, doubt and division.","author":"John Ruskin","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:90"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0092","text":"It is a good thing for an uneducated man to read books of quotations. The quotations, when engraved upon the memory, give you good thoughts. They also make you anxious to read the authors and look for more.","author":"Winston Churchill","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:91"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0093","text":"Health food may be good for the conscience but Oreos taste a hell of a lot better.","author":"Robert Redford","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:92"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0094","text":"Keep your fears to yourself, but share your courage with others.","author":"Robert Lewis Stevenson","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:93"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0095","text":"You gain strength, courage, and confidence by every experience by which you really stop to look fear in the face. You are able to say to yourself, 'I lived through this horror. I can take the next thing that comes along.","author":"Eleanor Roosevelt","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:94"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0096","text":"God, grant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change, the courage to change the things I can, and the wisdom to know the difference.","author":"Reinhold Niebuhr","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:95"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0097","text":"Courage is grace under pressure.","author":"Ernest Hemingway","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:96"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0098","text":"Courage is not the towering oak that sees storms come and go; it is the fragile blossom that opens in the snow.","author":"Alice M. Swaim","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:97"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0099","text":"Healing takes courage, and we all have courage, even if we have to dig a little to find it.","author":"Tori Amos","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:98"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0100","text":"It often requires more courage to dare to do right than to fear to do wrong.","author":"Abraham Lincoln","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:99"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0101","text":"We gain strength, and courage, and confidence by each experience in which we really stop to look fear in the face ... we must do that which we think we cannot.","author":"Eleanor Roosevelt","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:100"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0102","text":"Courage is one step ahead of fear.","author":"Coleman Young","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:101"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0103","text":"Courage is not the absence of fear, but rather the judgment that something else is more important than fear.","author":"Ambrose Redmoon","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:102"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0104","text":"God, grant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change, courage to change the things I can, and the wisdom to know the difference.","author":"Rembrandt","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:103"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0105","text":"We must build dikes of courage to hold back the flood of fear.","author":"Martin Luther King, Jr","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:104"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0106","text":"Just as courage imperils life, fear protects it.","author":"Leonardo da Vinci","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:105"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0107","text":"Of all the observations I have made on the strike, none has brought forth so much heat and emotion as the stress and emphasis we put on non- violence. Our most loyal supporters, whose courage and devotion has never been doubted, unanimously and strenuously disagreed with this approach and with the assurances we gave that we would not use any form of intimidation whatsoever to induce people to stay away from work. It was argued that the soil of our beloved country has been stained with the priceless blood of African patriots murdered by the Nationalist government in the course of peaceful and disciplined demonstrations to assert their claims and legitimate aspirations.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:106"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0108","text":"God grant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change, the courage to change the things I can, and the wisdom to know the difference.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:107"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0109","text":"Count your smiles instead of your tears; Count your courage instead of your fears.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:108"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0110","text":"Curiosity will conquer fear even more than bravery will.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:109"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0111","text":"Slowness to change usually means fear of the new.","author":"Philip Crosby","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:110"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0112","text":"Don't fear change, embrace it.","author":"Anthony J. D'Angelo","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:111"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0113","text":"Other people do not have to change for us to experience peace of mind.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:112"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0114","text":"What the statesman is most anxious to produce is a certain moral character in his fellow citizens, namely a disposition to virtue and the performance of virtuous actions.","author":"Aristotle","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:113"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0115","text":"If we wish to create a lasting peace we must begin with the children.","author":"Mahatma Gandhi","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:114"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0116","text":"Men fear death as children fear to go in the dark; and as that natural fear in children is increased by tales, so is the other.","author":"Francis Bacon, Sr.","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:115"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0117","text":"I learned that you should feel when writing, not like Lord Byron on a mountain top, but like child stringing beads in kindergarten, - happy, absorbed and quietly putting one bead on after another.","author":"Brenda Ueland","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:116"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0118","text":"We need to teach the next generation of children from Day One that they are responsible for their lives. Mankind's greatest gift, also its greatest curse, is that we have free choice. We can make our choices built from love or from fear.","author":"Elisabeth Kubler-Ross","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:117"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0119","text":"God's love is ever and always, eternally present to all who fear him, making everything right for them and their children (Psalm 103:17).","author":"The Bible","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:118"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0120","text":"It is good to realize that if love and peace can prevail on earth, and if we can teach our children to honor nature's gifts, the joys and beauties of the outdoors will be here forever.","author":"Jimmy Carter","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:119"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0121","text":"A child does not have to be taught how to be happy or the ways of love. It is fear, hatred, & prejudice that have to be taught. And from the condition of the world we can see that unfortunately there are some very good teachers.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:120"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0122","text":"Sometimes I see myself as a child in a rain storm, running around trying to catch all the drops in his mouth. I long for your adventures to be like the raindrops the child saves and not those which crash to the ground.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:121"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0123","text":"Christmas is not a time nor a season, but a state of mind. To cherish peace and goodwill, to be plenteous in mercy, is to have the real spirit of Christmas.","author":"Calvin Coolidge","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:122"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0124","text":"The earth has grown old with its burden of care but at Christmas it always is young, The heart of the jewel burns lustrous and fair and its soul full of music breaks the air, when the song of angels is sung.","author":"Phillip Brooks","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:123"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0125","text":"Happy, happy Christmas, that can win us back to the delusions of our childhood days, recall to the old man the pleasures of his youth, and transport the traveler back to his own fireside and quiet home!","author":"Charles Dickens","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:124"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0126","text":"I heard the bells on Christmas Day; their old familiar carols play, and wild and sweet the word repeat of peace on earth, good-will to men!","author":"Henry Wadsworth Longfellow","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:125"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0127","text":"With every recurring Christmas morning the prospects of the world's peace grow brighter, and the practice of universal brotherhood comes a little nearer to the door.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:126"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0128","text":"There's more, much more, to Christmas Than candlelight and cheer; It's the spirit of sweet friendship That brightens all year. It's thoughtfulness and kindness, It's hope reborn again, For peace, for understanding, And for goodwill to men!","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:127"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0129","text":"Tell your heart that the fear of suffering is worse than the suffering itself. And no heart has ever suffered when it goes in search of its dream.","author":"Paulo Coelho","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:128"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0130","text":"Peace can be reached through meditation on the knowledge which dreams give. Peace can also be reached through concentration upon that which is dearest to the heart.","author":"Patanjali","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:129"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0131","text":"Never fear shadows. They simply mean there's a light shining somewhere nearby.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:130"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0132","text":"Only a brave person is willing to honestly admit, and fearlessly to face, what a sincere and logical mind discovers.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:131"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0133","text":"The optimist thinks this is the best of all possible worlds. The pessimist fears it is true.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:132"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0134","text":"Love is the life of our heart. According to it, we desire, rejoice, hope and despair, fear, take heart, hate, avoid things, feel sad, grow angry, and exult.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:133"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0135","text":"Everything we do in life is based upon fear, especially love.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:134"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0136","text":"I can't control my destiny, I trust my soul, my only goal is just to be. There's only now, there's only here. Give in to love or live in fear. No other path, no other way. No day but today.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:135"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0137","text":"The optimist proclaims we live in the best of all possible worlds; and the pessimist fears this is true.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:136"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0138","text":"Love is what we were born with. Fear is what we learned here.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:137"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0139","text":"Confront your fears, list them, get to know them, and only then will you be able to put them aside and move ahead.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:138"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0140","text":"There are no guarantees. From the viewpoint of fear, none are strong enough. From the viewpoint of love, none are necessary.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:139"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0141","text":"You never conquer a mountain. Mountains can't be conquered; you conquer yourself your hopes, your fears.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:140"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0142","text":"Fear can keep us up all night long, but faith makes one fine pillow.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:141"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0143","text":"Kill the snake of doubt in your soul, crush the worms of fear in your heart and mountains will move out of your way.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:142"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0144","text":"The free man is he who does not fear to go to the end of his thought.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:143"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0145","text":"You may feel like dwelling on your limits or your fears. Don't do it. A perfect prescription for a squandered, unfulfilled life is to accommodate self-defeating feelings while undercutting your finest, most productive ones.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:144"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0146","text":"Fear is that little darkroom where negatives are developed.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:145"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0147","text":"Today the nations of the world may be divided into two classes - the nations in which the government fears the people, and the nations in which the people fear the government.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:146"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0148","text":"To fight fear, act. To increase fear","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:147"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0149","text":"The optimist thinks this is the best of all worlds. The pessimist fears it is true.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:148"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0150","text":"Don't fear failure so much that you refuse to try new things. The saddest summary of a life contains three descriptions: could have, might have, and should have.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:149"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0151","text":"The worst sorrows in life are not in its losses and misfortunes, but its fears.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:150"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0152","text":"If fear alters behavior, you're already defeated.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:151"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0153","text":"Do not fear risk. All exploration, all growth is calculated. Without challenge people cannot reach their higher selves. Only if we are willing to walk over the edge can we become winners.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:152"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0154","text":"There is no fear in love; but perfect love casteth out fear.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:153"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0155","text":"We dance for laughter, we dance for tears, we dance for madness, we dance for fears, we dance for hopes, we dance for screams, we are the dancers, we create the dreams.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:154"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0156","text":"If we deny love that is given to us, if we refuse to give love because we fear pain or loss, then our lives will be empty, our loss greater.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:155"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0157","text":"There is no fear in love; but perfect love drives out fear.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:156"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0158","text":"I believe one of the hardest things you can do is conquer your fears, but if you have a goal, then itis your job to open up and let it be real no matter how scary it seems.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:157"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0159","text":"Truth fears no questions.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:158"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0160","text":"What man does not understand, he fears; and what he fears, he tends to destroy.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:159"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0161","text":"A pessimist is one who feels bad when he feels good for fear he'll feel worse when he feels better.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:160"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0162","text":"Never fear shadows. They simply mean there is a light shining somewhere nearby.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:161"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0163","text":"Too many of us stay closed up because we are too afraid to care too much, for fear the other does not care as much ... or at all.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:162"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0164","text":"The chemist who can extract from his heart's elements compassion, respect, longing, patience, regret, surprise, and forgiveness and compound them into one can create that atom which is called love.","author":"Kahlil Gibran","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:163"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0165","text":"When one has the feeling of dislike for evil, when one feels tranquil, one finds pleasure in listening to good teachings; when one has these feelings and appreciates them, one is free of fear.","author":"Buddha","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:164"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0166","text":"If you listen to your fears, you will die never knowing what a great person you might have been.","author":"Robert H. Schuller","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:165"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0167","text":"I simply can't build my hopes on a foundation of confusion, misery and death ... I thinkOe peace and tranquillity will return again.","author":"Anne Frank","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:166"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0168","text":"The hope of a secure and livable world lies with disciplined nonconformists who are dedicated to justice, peace and brotherhood.","author":"Martin Luther King, Jr","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:167"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0169","text":"Fear less, hope more; eat less, chew more; whine less, breath more; talk less, say more, and all good things will be yours.","author":"Proverb","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:168"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0170","text":"Don't worry about people stealing your ideas. If your ideas are any good, you'll have to ram them down people's throats.","author":"Howard Aiken","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:169"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0171","text":"Ideas are the mightiest influence on earth. One great thought breathed into a man may regenerate him.","author":"William Ellery Channing","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:170"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0172","text":"Peace and justice are two sides of the same coin.","author":"Dwight David Eisenhower","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:171"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0173","text":"Reconciliation should be accompanied by justice, otherwise it will not last. While we all hope for peace it shouldn't be peace at any cost but peace based on principle, on justice.","author":"Corazon Aquino","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:172"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0174","text":"Peace is the work of justice indirectly, in so far as justice removes the obstacles to peace; but it is the work of charity (love) directly, since charity, according to its very notion, causes peace.","author":"St. Thomas Aquinas","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:173"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0175","text":"Peace will not come out of a clash of arms but out of justice lived and done by unarmed nations in the face of odds.","author":"Mahatma Gandhi","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:174"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0176","text":"Peace is more important than all justice; and peace was not made for the sake of justice, but justice for the sake of peace.","author":"Martin Luther","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:175"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0177","text":"Justice is not to be taken by storm. She is to be wooed by slow advances.","author":"Benjamin Cardozo","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:176"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0178","text":"The love of justice in most men is only the fear of themselves suffering by injustice.","author":"FranAois de la Rochefoucauld","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:177"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0179","text":"Love feels no burden, thinks nothing of trouble, attempts what is above its strength, pleads no excuse of impossibility; for it thinks all things lawful for itself, and all things possible.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:178"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0180","text":"For a community to be whole and healthy, it must be based on people's love and concern for each other.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:179"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0181","text":"When our eyes see our hands doing the work of our hearts, the circle of Creation is completed inside us, the doors of our souls fly open, and love steps forth to heal everything in sight.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:180"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0182","text":"The spiritual meaning of love is measured by what it can do. Love is meant to heal. Love is meant to renew. Love is meant to bring us closer to God.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:181"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0183","text":"When we are capable of living in the moment free from the tyranny of \"shoulds,\" free from the nagging sensation that this moment isn't right, we will have peaceful hearts.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:182"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0184","text":"Fear is the main source of superstition, and one of the main sources of cruelty. To conquer fear is the beginning of wisdom, in the pursuit of truth as in the endeavour after a worthy manner of life.","author":"Bertrand Russell","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:183"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0185","text":"Better a lie which heals than a truth which wounds.","author":"Proverb","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:184"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0186","text":"Peace if possible, truth at all costs.","author":"Martin Luther","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:185"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0187","text":"In battling evil, excess is good; for he who is moderate in announcing the truth is presenting half-truth. He conceals the other half out of fear of the people's wrath.","author":"Kahlil Gibran","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:186"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0188","text":"In quiet moments when you think about it, you recognize what is critically important in life and what isn't. Be wise and don't let good things crowd out those that are essential.","author":"Elder Richard G. Scott","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:187"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0189","text":"The heart of the wise man lies quiet like limpid water.","author":"Proverb","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:188"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0190","text":"The wise man ... if he would live at peace with others, he will bear and forbear.","author":"Samuel Smiles","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:189"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0191","text":"The fear of the Lord is the beginning of wisdom (Psalms 111:10).","author":"The Bible","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:190"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0192","text":"Dreaming permits each and every one of us to be quietly and safely insane every night of our lives.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:191"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0193","text":"The principle office of history I take to be this: to prevent virtuous actions from being forgotten, and that evil words and deeds should fear an infamous reputation with posterity.","author":"Publius Cornelius Tacitus","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:192"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0194","text":"An insincere and evil friend is more to be feared than a wild beast; a wild beast may wound your body, but an evil friend will wound your mind.","author":"Buddha","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:193"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0195","text":"The fear of the LORD tendeth to life: and he that hath it shall abide satisfied; he shall not be visited with evil (Proverbs 19:23).","author":"The Bible","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:194"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0196","text":"One must be out-of-doors enough to get experience of wholesome reality, as a ballast to thought and sentiment. Health requires this relaxation, this aimless life.","author":"Henry David Thoreau","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:195"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0197","text":"My experience through life has convinced me that, while moderation and temperance in all things are commendable and beneficial, abstinence from spirituous liquors is the best safeguard of morals and health.","author":"Robert E. Lee","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:196"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0198","text":"I do not fear failure. I only fear the \"slowing up\" of the engine inside of me which is pounding, saying, \"Keep going, someone must be on top, why not you?\"","author":"George S. Patton","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:197"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0199","text":"I'm proof against that word failure. I've seen behind it. The only failure a man ought to fear is failure of cleaving to the purpose he sees to be best.","author":"T. S. Eliot","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:198"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0200","text":"The only failure a man ought to fear is failure in cleaving to the purpose he sees to be best.","author":"T. S. Eliot","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:199"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0201","text":"The person interested in success has to learn to view failure as a healthy, inevitable part of the process of getting to the top.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:200"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0202","text":"It distresses me, this failure to keep pace with the leaders of thought, as they pass into oblivion","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:201"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0203","text":"Faith is an invisible and invincible magnet, and attracts to itself whatever it fervently desires and calmly and persistently expects.","author":"Ralph Waldo Trine","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:202"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0204","text":"Every tomorrow has two handles. We can take hold of it with the handle of anxiety or the handle of faith.","author":"Henry Ward Beecher","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:203"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0205","text":"Homelessness is not just an isolated social evil. It is the catalyst and the breeding ground for other problems such as marriage difficulties and family breakup, stress, unemployment and alcoholism..","author":"General Eva Burrows","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:204"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0206","text":"I wish my mother had told me the same thing about horror movies and guys when I was little- 'Don't worry, honey, it's all fake.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:205"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0207","text":"A healthy family is sacred territory.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:206"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0208","text":"Nothing in life is to be feared. It is only to be understood.","author":"Marie Curie","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:207"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0209","text":"Do not fear death so much but rather the inadequate life.","author":"Bertolt Brecht","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:208"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0210","text":"The man who fears no truth has nothing to fear from lies.","author":"Thomas Jefferson","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:209"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0211","text":"Where fear is, happiness is not.","author":"Seneca","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:210"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0212","text":"The greatest mistake we make is living in constant fear that we will make one.","author":"John Maxwell","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:211"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0213","text":"The optimist proclaims that we live in the best of all possible worlds; and the pessimist fears this is true.","author":"James Branch Cabell","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:212"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0214","text":"They can conquer who believe they can. He has not learned the first lesson in life who does not every day surmount a fear.","author":"Ralph Waldo Emerson","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:213"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0215","text":"He who is not everyday conquering some fear has not learned the secret of life.","author":"Ralph Waldo Emerson","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:214"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0216","text":"Those who own much have much to fear","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:215"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0217","text":"The fear of death is more to be dreaded then fear itself.","author":"Publilius Syrus","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:216"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0218","text":"The only thing we have to fear is fear itself.","author":"Franklin D. Roosevelt","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:217"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0219","text":"Fear is the thought of admitted inferiority.","author":"Elbert Hubbard","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:218"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0220","text":"There is no feeling, except the extremes of fear and grief, that does not find relief in music.","author":"T. S. Eliot","source":"Stress Relief Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Stress Relief","sequence:219"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0221","text":"Teaching music is not my main purpose. I want to make good citizens. If children hear fine music from the day of their birth and learn to play it, they develop sensitivity, discipline and endurance. They get a beautiful heart.","author":"Shinichi Suzuki","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:220"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0222","text":"All successful people men and women are big dreamers. They imagine what their future could be, ideal in every respect, and then they work every day toward their distant vision, that goal or purpose.","author":"Brian Tracy","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:221"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0223","text":"Success is the result of perfection, hard work, learning from failure, loyalty, and persistence.","author":"Colin Powell","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:222"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0224","text":"Many school focus too much on achievement ... (they need) to create opportunities for young people develop their learning muscles and their learning stamina through working on real problems ... to reflect on and manage their own learning","author":"Guy Claxton","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:223"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0225","text":"The key is to replace a belief in 'experts' who 'deliver' knowledge of what good teaching is to workshops with communities of teachers who learn through ongoing collaboration and practice","author":"Dennis Sparks","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:224"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0226","text":"Genius is only the power of making continuous efforts. The line between failure and success is so fine that we scarcely know when we pass it: so fine that we are often on the line and do not know it. How many a man has thrown up his hands at a time when a little more effort, a little more patience, would have achieved success. As the tide goes out, so it comes clear in. In business, sometimes, prospects may seem darkest when really they are on the turn. A little more persistence, a little more effort, and what seemed hopeless failure may turn to glorious success. There is no failure except in no longer trying. There is no defeat except from within, no really insurmountable barrier save our own inherent weakness of purpose.","author":"Elbert Hubbard","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:225"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0227","text":"Firmness of purpose is one of the most necessary sinews of character, and one of the best instruments of success. Without it genius wastes its efforts in a maze of inconsistencies.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:226"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0228","text":"Thoughts lead on to purposes; purposes go forth in action; actions form habits; habits decide character; and character fixes our destiny.","author":"Tryon Edwards","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:227"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0229","text":"Leaders aren't born, they are made. And they are made just like anything else, through hard work. And that's the price we'll have to pay to achieve that goal, or any goal.","author":"Vince Lombardi","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:228"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0230","text":"Leaders are made, they are not born. They are made by hard effort, which is the price which all of us must pay to achieve any goal that is worthwhile.","author":"Vince Lombardi","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:229"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0231","text":"Respect your fellow human being, treat them fairly, disagree with them honestly, enjoy their friendship, explore your thoughts about one another candidly, work together for a common goal and help one another achieve it.","author":"Bill Bradley","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:230"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0232","text":"Never regard study as a duty, but as the enviable opportunity to learn to know the liberating influence of beauty in the realm of the spirit for your own personal joy and to the profit of the community to which your later work belongs.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:231"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0233","text":"Individual commitment to a group effort, that is what makes a team work, a company work, a society work, a civilization work.","author":"Vince Lombardi","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:232"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0234","text":"Efforts and courage are not enough without purpose and direction.","author":"John Fitzgerald Kennedy","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:233"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0235","text":"One isn't necessarily born with courage, but one is born with potential. Without courage, we cannot practice any other virtue with consistency. We can't be kind, true, merciful, generous, or honest.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:234"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0236","text":"I feel certain that the personal computer is as revolutionary in terms of the way it will change the way we work, learn, and entertain ourselves as any of these previous advances.","author":"Bill Gates","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:235"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0237","text":"Goals are simply tools to focus your energy in positive directions, these can be changed as your priorities change, new one added, and others dropped.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:236"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0238","text":"Practical wisdom is only to be learned in the school of experience. Precepts and instruction are useful so far as they go, but, without the discipline of real life, they remain of the nature of theory only.","author":"Samuel Smiles","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:237"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0239","text":"The purpose of a liberal arts education is to learn that a person can like both cats and dogs!","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:238"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0240","text":"I am convinced that the teaching of the church is in theory a crafty and evil lie, and in practice a concoction of gross superstition and witchcraft","author":"Leo Nikolaevich Tolstoy","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:239"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0241","text":"Ignorance of all things is an evil neither terrible nor excessive, nor yet the greatest of all; but great cleverness and much learning, if they be accompanied by a bad training, are a much greater misfortune.","author":"Plato","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:240"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0242","text":"There are no secrets to success. It is the result of preparation, hard work, and learning from failure.","author":"Colin Powell","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:241"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0243","text":"A little more persistence, a little more effort, and what seemed hopeless failure may turn to glorious success.","author":"Elbert Hubbard","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:242"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0244","text":"Remember the two benefits of failure. First, if you do fail, you learn what doesn't work; and second, the failure gives you the opportunity to try a new approach.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:243"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0245","text":"Teach us, O Lord, the disciplines of patience, for to wait is often harder than to work.","author":"Peter Marshall","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:244"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0246","text":"I have always grown from my problems and challenges, from the things that don't work out, that's when I've really learned.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:245"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0247","text":"It behooves every man to remember that the work of the critic, is of altogether secondary importance, and that, in the end, progress is accomplished by the man who does things.","author":"Theodore Roosevelt","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:246"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0248","text":"A child born to a black mother in a state like Mississippi ... has exactly the same rights as a white baby born to the wealthiest person in the United States. It's not true, but I challenge anyone to say it is not a goal worth working for.","author":"Tiger Woods","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:247"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0249","text":"A new vision of development is emerging. Development is becoming a people-centered process, whose ultimate goal must be the improvement of the human condition.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:248"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0250","text":"All growth depends upon activity. There is no development physically or intellectually without effort, and effort means work.","author":"Calvin Coolidge","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:249"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0251","text":"Without continual growth and progress, such words as improvement, achievement, and success have no meaning.","author":"Benjamin Franklin","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:250"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0252","text":"Without some goal and some efforts to reach it, no man can live.","author":"Fyodor Dostoyevsky","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:251"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0253","text":"Discipline is the bridge between goals and accomplishments","author":"Jim Rohn","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:252"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0254","text":"Thank God, I have my work, but instead of earning money by it, I need money to be able to work; that is the difficulty. I think there are no signs in my work that indicate that I shall fail. And I am not a person who works slowly or tamely. Drawing becomes a passion with me, and I throw myself into it more and more. I do not have great plans for the future; if for a moment I feel rising within me the desire for a life without care, for prosperity, each time I go fondly back to the trouble and the cares, to a life full of hardship, and think: It is better so; I learn more from it, and make progress. This is not the road on which one perishes. I only hope the trouble and the cares will not become unbearable, and I have confidence I shall succeed in earning enough to keep myself, not in luxury, but as one who eats his bread in the sweat of his brow.","author":"Vincent Van Gogh","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:253"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0255","text":"Why does this applied science, which saves work and makes life easier, bring us so little happiness? The simple answer runs: Because we have not yet learned to make sensible use of it.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:254"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0256","text":"Learned institutions ought to be favorite objects with every free people. They throw that light over the public mind which is the best security against crafty and dangerous encroachments on the public liberty.","author":"James Madison","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:255"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0257","text":"All of us are guinea pigs in the laboratory of God. Humanity is just a work in progress.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:256"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0258","text":"The soul, like the body, accepts by practice whatever habit one wishes it to contact.","author":"Socrates","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:257"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0259","text":"Work joyfully and peacefully, knowing that right thoughts and right efforts will inevitably bring about right results.","author":"James Allen","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:258"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0260","text":"The way to learn to do things is to do things. The way to learn a trade is to work at it. Success teaches how to succeed. Begin with the determination to succeed, and the work is half done already.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:259"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0261","text":"Beware of the man who works hard to learn something, learns it, and finds himself no wiser than before. He is full of murderous resentment of people who are ignorant without having come by their ignorance the hard way.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:260"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0262","text":"Opportunity follows struggle. It follows effort. It follows hard work. It doesn't come before.","author":"Shelby Steele","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:261"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0263","text":"Respect your efforts, respect yourself. Self-respect leads to self-discipline. When you have both firmly under your belt, that's real power.","author":"Clint Eastwood","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:262"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0264","text":"The biggest job we have is to teach a newly hired employee how to fail intelligently. We have to train him to experiment over and over and to keep on trying and failing until he learns what will work.","author":"Charles F. Kettering","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:263"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0265","text":"Concentrate all your thoughts upon the work at hand. The sun's rays do not burn until brought to a focus.","author":"Alexander Graham Bell","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:264"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0266","text":"Till a man can judge whether they be truths or not, his understanding is but little improved, and thus men of much reading, though greatly learned, but may be little knowing.","author":"John Locke","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:265"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0267","text":"I learned the value of hard work by working hard.","author":"Margaret Mead","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:266"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0268","text":"It's all very well in practice, but it will never work in theory.","author":"French Proverb","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:267"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0269","text":"Of all the things I have done, the most vital is coordinating the talents of those who work for us and pointing them towards a certain goal.","author":"Walt Disney","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:268"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0270","text":"The best performance improvement is the transition from the nonworking state to the working state.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:269"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0271","text":"A good tool improves the way you work. A great tool improves the way you think","author":"Jeff Duntemann","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:270"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0272","text":"A good tool improves the way you work.&nbsp; A great tool improves the way you think.","author":"Jeff Duntemann","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:271"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0273","text":"A teacher's failure to create an intellectually reflective, engagement for learning is not simply malpractice but it is immoral particularly for students who cannot withdraw","author":"John Goodland","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:272"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0274","text":"If we want to create a workplace that values idealism, human connection, and real, in depth learning, we will have to create it ourselves","author":"Peter Block","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:273"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0275","text":"Passion mutates into procedures, into rules and roles. Instead of purpose, we focus on policies. Instead of being free to create, we impose constraints that squeeze the life out of us","author":"Margaret Wheatley and Kellner Rogers","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:274"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0276","text":"Powerful learning strategies can most simply be thought of what we presently do for gifted and talented children. What works for them works just as well for 'at risk' students","author":"Henry M Levin","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:275"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0277","text":"School improvement is most surely and thoroughly achieved when teachers engage in frequent, continuous and increasingly concrete talk about teaching practices ... capable of distinguishing one practice and it's virtue from another","author":"Judith Warren","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:276"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0278","text":"Some schools develop 'toxic' cultures which actively discourage efforts to improve teaching or student achievement","author":"Deal and Patterson 98","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:277"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0279","text":"Something magical happens when you bring together a group of people from different disciplines with a common purpose","author":"Mark Stefik","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:278"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0280","text":"The value of an education in a liberal arts college is not the learning of many facts, but the training of the mind to think something that cannot be learned from textbooks.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:279"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0281","text":"we know at lot more now than the 'last time around'- the 1960s and 1970s - about how to work for smart schools ... 'The smart school finds it's foundation in a rich and evolving set of principles about human thinking and learning","author":"David Perkins","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:280"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0282","text":"The reason most people never reach their goals is that they don't define them, learn about them, or even seriously consider them as believable or achievable. Winners can tell you where they are going, what they plan to do along the way, and who will be sharing the adventure with them.","author":"Denis Waitley","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:281"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0283","text":"A person should set his goals as early as he can and devote all his energy and talent to getting there. With enough effort, he may achieve it. Or he may find something that is even more rewarding. But in the end, no matter what the outcome, he will know he has been alive.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:282"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0284","text":"Excellence is an art won by training and habituation. We do not act rightly because we have virtue or excellence, but we rather have those because we have acted rightly. We are what we repeatedly do. Excellence, then, is not an act but a habit.","author":"Aristotle","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:283"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0285","text":"Any great work of art . . . revives and readapts time and space, and the measure of its success is the extent to which it makes you an inhabitant of that world -- the extent to which it invites you in and lets you breathe its strange, special air.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:284"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0286","text":"I regard it as a duty which I owed, not just to my people, but also to my profession, to the practice of law, and to the justice for all mankind, to cry out against this discrimination which is essentially unjust and opposed to the whole basis of the attitude towards justice which is part of the tradition of legal training in this country. I believed that in taking up a stand against this injustice I was upholding the dignity of what should be an honorable profession.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:285"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0287","text":"With the affairs of active human beings it is different. Here knowledge of truth alone does not suffice; on the contrary this knowledge must continually be renewed by ceaseless effort, if it is not to be lost. It resembles a statue of marble which stan ds in the desert and is continuously threatened with burial by the shifting sands. The hands of science must ever be at work in order that the marble column continue everlastingly to shine in the sun. To those serving hands mine also belong.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:286"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0288","text":"Progress, far from consisting in change, depends on retentiveness. When change is absolute there remains no being to improve and no direction is set for possible improvement: and when experience is not retained, as among savages, infancy is perpetual.","author":"George Santayana","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:287"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0289","text":"Perhaps the most valuable result of all education is the ability to make yourself do the thing you have to do, when it ought to be done, whether you like it or not. It is the first lesson that ought to be learned and however early a man's training begins, it is probably the last lesson that he learns thoroughly.","author":"Thomas Henry Huxley","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:288"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0290","text":"As death, when we come to consider it closely, is the true goal of our existence, I have formed during the last few years such close relations with this best and truest friend of mankind, that his image is not only no longer terrifying to me, but is indeed very soothing and consoling! And I thank my God for graciously granting me the opportunity of learning that death is the key which unlocks the door to our true happiness.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:289"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0291","text":"It would be difficult for me to express all my thoughts about it. It remains a constant disappointment to me that my drawings are not yet what I want them to be. The difficulties are indeed numerous and great, and cannot be overcome immediately. Making progress is like miners' work: it doesn't advance as quickly as one should like, and also as others expect; but faced with such a task, patience and faithfulness are essential. In fact, I don't think much about the difficulties, because if one thought of them too much, one would get dazed or confused.","author":"Vincent Van Gogh","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:290"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0292","text":"You cannot hope to build a better world without improving the individuals. To that end, each of us must work for our own improvement and, at the same time, share a general responsibility for all humanity, our particular duty being to aid those to whom we think we can be most useful.","author":"Marie Curie","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:291"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0293","text":"It is important to do what you don't know how to do. It is important to see your skills as keeping you from learning what is deepest and most mysterious. If you know how to focus, unfocus. If your tendency is to make sense out of chaos, start chaos.","author":"Carlos Casteneda","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:292"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0294","text":"What we need to do is learn to work in the system, by which I mean that everybody, every team, every platform, every division, every component is there not for individual competitive profit or recognition, but for contribution to the system as a whole on a win-win basis.","author":"W. Edwards Deming","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:293"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0295","text":"When we are working at a difficult task and strive after a good thing, we are fighting a righteous battle, the direct reward of which is that we are kept from much evil. As we advance in life it becomes more and more difficult, but in fighting the difficulties the inmost strength of the heart is developed. Indeed life is a have to defend and protect ourselves, and with a cheerful and brace spirit we must battle; we plan and calculate in order to make progress.","author":"Vincent Van Gogh","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:294"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0296","text":"Bear in mind that the wonderful things you learn in your schools are the work of many generations. All this is put in your hands as your inheritance in order that you may receive it, honor it, add to it, and one day faithfully hand it on to your children.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:295"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0297","text":"Nature is not cruel, pitilessly, indifferent. This is one of the hardest lessons for humans to learn. We cannot admit that things might be neither good nor evil, neither cruel nor kind, but simply callous -- indifferent to all suffering, lacking all purpose.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:296"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0298","text":"Writing, at its best, is a lonely life. Organizations for writers palliate the writer's loneliness, but I doubt if they improve his writing. He grows in public stature as he sheds his loneliness and often his work deteriorates. For he does his work alone and if he is a good enough writer he must face eternity, or the lack of it, each day.","author":"Ernest Hemingway","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:297"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0299","text":"the challenge ( for leadership) is to initiate a conversation about what's purpose and what's just practice. Preserve the best, reinvent the rest' ... Hold your company hostage, declare your vision in a public way ... Make decisions right or wrong .There is nothing worse than waffling","author":"Keith Yamashira","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:298"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0300","text":"For too long schools have had to comply with endless bureaucratic top down edicts, confusing curriculums and associated accountability demands which have taken the focus away from learning and teaching. As these imposed technocratic systems falter it is now time for creative teachers to also add their voices to the debate","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:299"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0301","text":"I think it is important for leaders to answer the question 'What's exciting about the work I /we really do here?' ..to expand it out to the higher meaning and purpose ... To really articulate what we really do here, and why this place is cool.'","author":"Steve Farber","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:300"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0302","text":"Progress seldom leads to serenity, nor should it. A serene workforce is unlikely to try new things .Creative workers gripe a lot but at a high level ... They are concerned about having the leeway and support to be create something new. They want their talents to be utilized. They crave a challenge","author":"Farston and Keynes","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:301"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0303","text":"Studies of high school gradates rarely find any correlation between recognition in high school and recognition thereafter ... The term s are too different. What worked in high school seldom works later ... Those not tested by setbacks when young may never learn how to rebound from defeat","author":"Farson and Keyes","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:302"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0304","text":"We can create our own characters and write our own script, if properly taught: 'In a very real sense ... human being create themselves' and school can be stage on which children work through the plot, rehearse their roles, learn the cues, create social functions, try out their 'ideal selves' for size, play hero parts which demonstrate their capability for greatness","author":"Jerry Starratt Expert School Leadership","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:303"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0305","text":"Talent finds its models, methods, and ends in society, exists for exhibition, and goes to the soul only for power to work. Genius is its own end, and draws its means and the style of its architecture from within.","author":"Ralph Waldo Emerson","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:304"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0306","text":"Talent works, genius creates.","author":"Robert A. Schumann","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:305"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0307","text":"It is the curse of talent that, although it labors with greater steadiness and perseverance than genius, it does not reach its goal, while genius already on the summit of the ideal, gazes laughingly about.","author":"Robert A. Schumann","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:306"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0308","text":"Genius begins great works; labor alone finishes them.","author":"Joseph Joubert","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:307"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0309","text":"Genius ... means little more than the faculty of perceiving in an unhabitual way.","author":"William James","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:308"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0310","text":"What a piece of work is a man! How noble in reason, how infinite in faculty, in form and moving how express and admirable, in action how like an angel, in apprehension how like a god -- the beauty of the world, the paragon of animals!","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:309"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0311","text":"As you begin changing your thinking, start immediately to change your behaviour. Begin to act the part of the person you would like to become. Take action on your behaviour. Too many people want to feel, then take action. This never works.","author":"John Maxwell","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:310"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0312","text":"Leadership is practiced not so much in words as in attitude and in actions.","author":"Harold S. Geneen","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:311"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0313","text":"Satisfaction lies in the effort, not in the attainment, full effort is full victory.","author":"Mahatma Gandhi","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:312"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0314","text":"To will is to select a goal, determine a course of action that will bring one to that goal, and then hold tothat action till the goal is reached. The key is action.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:313"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0315","text":"To manage a system effectively, you might focus on the interactions of the parts rather than their behavior taken separately.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:314"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0316","text":"Attitudes are nothing more than habits of thoughts, and habits can be acquired. An action repeated becomes an attitude realized.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:315"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0317","text":"Happiness does not come from doing easy work but from the afterglow of satisfaction that comes after the achievement of a difficult task that demanded our best.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:316"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0318","text":"The atom, being for all practical purposes the stable unit of the physical plane, is a constantly changing vortex of reactions.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:317"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0319","text":"Nothing can stop the man with the right mental attitude from achieving his goal; nothing on earth can help the man with the wrong mental attitude.","author":"Thomas Jefferson","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:318"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0320","text":"What you get by achieving your goals is to as important as what you become by achieving your goals.","author":"Zig Ziglar","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:319"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0321","text":"appiness ... it lies in the joy of achievement, in the thrill of creative effort.","author":"Franklin D. Roosevelt","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:320"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0322","text":"Think little goals and expect little achievements. Think big goals and win big success.","author":"David Joseph Schwartz","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:321"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0323","text":"I don't want to achieve immortality through my work. I want to achieve it through not dying.","author":"Woody Allen","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:322"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0324","text":"I report to you that our country is challenged at home and abroad: that it is our will that is being tried and not our strength; our sense of purpose and not our ability to achieve a better America.","author":"Lyndon B. Johnson","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:323"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0325","text":"Achievement is not always success, while reputed failure often is. It is honest endeavor, persistent effort to do the best possible under any and all circumstances.","author":"Orison Sweet Marden","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:324"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0326","text":"The three great essentials to achieve anything worth while are, first, hard work; second, stick-to-itiveness; third, common sense.","author":"Thomas Alva Edison","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:325"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0327","text":"If you want to achieve excellence, you can get there today. As of this second, quit doing less-than-excellent work.","author":"Thomas J. Watson, Sr.","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:326"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0328","text":"Setting a goal is not the main thing. It is deciding how you will go about achieving it and staying with that plan.","author":"Tom Landry","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:327"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0329","text":"I feel sorry for the person who can't get genuinely excited about his work. Not only will he never be satisfied, but he will never achieve anything worthwhile.","author":"Walter Chrysler","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:328"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0330","text":"First, have a definite, clear practical ideal; a goal, an objective. Second, have the necessary means to achieve your ends; wisdom, money, materials, and methods. Third, adjust all your means to that end.","author":"Aristotle","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:329"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0331","text":"I'm a great believer that any tool that enhances communication has profound effects in terms of how people can learn from each other, and how they can achieve the kind of freedoms that they're interested in.","author":"Bill Gates","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:330"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0332","text":"I never allow myself to become discouraged under any circumstances. The three great essentials to achieve anything worthwhile are first, hard work, second, stick-to-ittiveness, third, common sense.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:331"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0333","text":"They are not following dharma who resort to violence to achieve their purpose. But those who lead others through nonviolent means, knowing right and wrong, may be called guardians of the dharma.","author":"Buddha","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:332"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0334","text":"The greater the loyalty of a group toward the group, the greater is the motivation among the members to achieve the goals of the group, and the greater the probability that the group will achieve its goals.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:333"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0335","text":"For those who play the game, an hour may be a year, a single day's work an achievement for eternity.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:334"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0336","text":"Set priorities for your goals. A major part of successful living lies in the ability to put first things first. Indeed, the reason most major goals are not achieved is that we spend our time doing second things first.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:335"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0337","text":"Every great work, every big accomplishment, has been brought into manifestation through holding to the vision, and often just before the big achievement, comes apparent failure and discouragement.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:336"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0338","text":"Perfections of mean and confusion of goals seem -in my opinion- to characterize our age.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:337"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0339","text":"Of middle age the best that can be said is that a middle-aged person has likely learned how to have a little fun in spite of his troubles.","author":"Donald R. Perry Marquis","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:338"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0340","text":"For the unlearned, old age is winter; for the learned it is the season of the harvest.","author":"The Talmud","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:339"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0341","text":"Old age hath yet his honor and his toil. Death closes all; but something ere the end, Some work of noble note, may yet be done, Not unbecoming men that strove with Gods.","author":"Alfred, Lord Tennyson","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:340"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0342","text":"Men and women approaching retirement age should be recycled for public service work, and their companies should foot the bill. We can no longer afford to scrap-pile people.","author":"Mahatma Gandhi","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:341"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0343","text":"In youth we learn; in age we understand.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:342"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0344","text":"The excitement of learning separates youth from old age. As long as you're learning you're not old.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:343"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0345","text":"Wisdom doesn't automatically come with old age. Nothing does - except wrinkles. It's true, some wines improve with age. But only if the grapes were good in the first place.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:344"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0346","text":"Art is not a handicraft, it is the transmission of feeling the artist has experienced.","author":"Leo Nikolaevich Tolstoy","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:345"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0347","text":"A work of art that contains theories is like an object on which the price tag has been left.","author":"Marcel Proust","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:346"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0348","text":"Art never improves, but . . . the material of art is never quite the same.","author":"T. S. Eliot","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:347"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0349","text":"Art is a human activity having for its purpose the transmission to others of the highest and best feelings to which men have risen.","author":"Leo Nikolaevich Tolstoy","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:348"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0350","text":"The whole art of teaching is only the art of awakening the natural curiosity of young minds for the purpose of satisfying it afterwards.","author":"Anatole France","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:349"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0351","text":"Works of art, in my opinion, are the only objects in the material universe to possess internal order, and that is why, though I don't believe that only art matters, I do belive in Art for Art's sake.","author":"E. M. Forster","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:350"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0352","text":"The purpose of art is to lay bare the questions which have been hidden by the answers.","author":"James Baldwin","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:351"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0353","text":"Religion is the masterpiece of the art of animal training, for it trains people as to how they shall think.","author":"Arthur Schopenhauer","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:352"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0354","text":"I feel I cannot touch humanity, even in thought, it is abhorrent to me. But a work of art is an act of faith, as Michael Angelo says, and one goes on writing, to the unseen witnesses.","author":"D. H. Lawrence","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:353"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0355","text":"To improve the golden moment of opportunity, and catch the good that is within our reach, is the great art of life.","author":"Samuel Johnson","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:354"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0356","text":"Paul, thou art beside thyself; much learning doth make thee mad. (Acts 26:26)","author":"The Bible","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:355"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0357","text":"The Lord recompense thy work, and a full reward be given thee of the Lord God of Israel, under whose wings thou art come to trust. (Ruth 2:12)","author":"The Bible","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:356"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0358","text":"The work of art must seize upon you, wrap you up in itself and carry you away. It is the means by which the artist conveys his passion. It is the current which he puts forth, which sweeps you along in his passion","author":"Auguste Renoir","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:357"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0359","text":"Many secrets of art and nature are thought by the unlearned to be magical.","author":"Francis Bacon, Sr.","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:358"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0360","text":"To know how to grow old is the master work of wisdom, and one of the most difficult chapters in the great art of living.","author":"Henri FrEdEric Amiel","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:359"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0361","text":"Art is not in some far-off place. A work of Art is the expression of a man's whole personality, sensibility and ability","author":"Shinichi Suzuki","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:360"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0362","text":"Good management is the art of making problems so interesting and their solutions so constructive that everyone wants to get to work and deal with them.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:361"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0363","text":"The art of progress is to preserve order amid change.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:362"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0364","text":"I like the fact that in ancient Chinese art the great painters always included a deliberate flaw in their work: human creation is never perfect.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:363"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0365","text":"In all the work we do, our most valuable asset can be the attitude of self-examination. It is forgivable to make mistakes, but to stand fast behind a wall of self-righteousness and make the same mistake twice is not forgivable.","author":"Dale E. Turner","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:364"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0366","text":"In the attitude of silence the soul finds the path in an clearer light, and what is elusive and deceptive resolves itself into crystal clearness. Our life is a long and arduous quest after Truth.","author":"Mahatma Gandhi","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:365"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0367","text":"Attitude is the way you mentally look at the world around you. It is how you view your environment and your future. It is the focus you develop toward life itself.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:366"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0368","text":"A positive attitude may not solve all your problems, but it will annoy enough people to make it worth the effort.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:367"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0369","text":"The authority of those who teach is often an obstacle to those who want to learn.","author":"Marcus Tullius Cicero","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:368"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0370","text":"Most men, after a little freedom, have preferred authority with the consoling assurances and the economy of effort it brings.","author":"Walter J. Lippmann","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:369"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0371","text":"I write for no other purpose than to add to the beauty that now belongs to me. I write a book for no other reason than to add three or four hundred acres to my magnificent estate.","author":"Jack London","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:370"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0372","text":"When I'm working on a problem, I never think about beauty. I think only how to solve the problem. But when I have finished, if the solution is not beautiful, I know it is wrong.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:371"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0373","text":"Character contributes to beauty. It fortifies a woman as her youth fades. A mode of conduct, a standard of courage, discipline, fortitude, and integrity can do a great deal to make a woman beautiful.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:372"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0374","text":"Practice Random Acts of Kindness and Senseless Beauty.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:373"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0375","text":"Keep on beginning and failing. Each time you fail, start all over gain, and you will grow stronger until have accomplished a purpose - not the one you began with perhaps, but one you'll be glad to remember.","author":"Anne Sullivan","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:374"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0376","text":"All I really need to know about how to live and what to do and how to be I learned in kindergarten. Remember the Dick-and-Jane books and the first word you learned--the biggest word of all--look.","author":"Robert Fulghum","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:375"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0377","text":"Discipline must come through liberty. . . . We do not consider an individual disciplined only when he has been rendered as artificially silent as a mute and as immovable as a paralytic. He is an individual annihilated, not disciplined.","author":"Maria Montessori","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:376"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0378","text":"Motivation is everything. You can do the work of two people, but you can't be two people. Instead, you have to inspire the next guy down the line and get him to inspire his people.","author":"Lee Iacocca","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:377"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0379","text":"Motivation is what gets you started. Habit is what keeps you going.","author":"Jim Rohn","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:378"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0380","text":"Every man's work, whether it be literature or music or pictures or anything else, is always a portrait of himself, and the more he tries to conceal himself the more clearly will his character appear in spite of him.","author":"Samuel Butler","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:379"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0381","text":"Music exists for the purpose of growing an admirable heart","author":"Shinichi Suzuki","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:380"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0382","text":"Music fills the infinite between two souls. This has been muffled by the mist of our daily habits.","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:381"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0383","text":"When you work you are a flute through whose heart the whispering of the hours turns to music. Which of you would be a reed, dumb and silent, when all else sings together in unison?","author":"Kahlil Gibran","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:382"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0384","text":"Winning is not a sometime thing, it's an all time thing. You don't win once in a while, you don't do things right once in a while, you do them right all the time. Winning is habit. Unfortunately, so is losing.","author":"Vince Lombardi","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:383"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0385","text":"Winning is not everything, but the effort to win is.","author":"Zig Ziglar","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:384"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0386","text":"Winning is a habit. Unfortunately, so is losing.","author":"Vince Lombardi","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:385"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0387","text":"Wise are they who have learned these truths: Trouble is temporary. Time is tonic. Tribulation is a test tube.","author":"William Arthur Ward","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:386"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0388","text":"The wisest mind has something yet to learn.","author":"George Santayana","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:387"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0389","text":"Who is a wise man? He who learns of all men.","author":"The Talmud","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:388"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0390","text":"The wise learn many things from their enemies.","author":"Aristophanes","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:389"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0391","text":"No matter how carefully you plan your goals, they will never be more than pipe dreams unless you pursue them with gusto.","author":"W. Clement Stone","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:390"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0392","text":"A dream doesn't become reality through magic; it takes sweat, determination and hard work.","author":"Colin Powell","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:391"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0393","text":"Learn from your dreams what you lack.","author":"Lyndon B. Johnson","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:392"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0394","text":"You are never given a dream without also being given the power to make it true. You may have to work for it, however.","author":"Richard Bach","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:393"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0395","text":"Initiative is key. Anybody who wants to be somebody is going to work as hard as they can to fulfill that dream.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:394"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0396","text":"Dreams, ideas, and plans not only are an escape, they give me purpose, a reason to hang on.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:395"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0397","text":"Iim the kid who has this habit of dreaming. Sometimes gets me in trouble too. But the truth is I could no more stop dreaming, than I could make them all come true.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:396"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0398","text":"One of the characteristics of the dream is that nothing suprises us in it. With no regret, we agree to live in it with strangers, completely cut off from our habits and friends.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:397"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0399","text":"Friendship improves happiness, and abates misery, by doubling our joys, and dividing our grief.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:398"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0400","text":"This is the true joy in life -- being used for a purpose recognized by yourself as a mighty one ...","author":"George Bernard Shaw","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:399"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0401","text":"There will be 'two societies' in the future: high-paid knowledge workers and low-paid service workers.","author":"Bill Gates","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:400"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0402","text":"I have learned throughout my life as a composer chiefly through my mistakes and pursuits of false assumptions, not by my exposure to founts of wisdom and knowledge.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:401"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0403","text":"When the eyes say one thing and the tongue another, the practiced person relies on the language of the first.","author":"Ralph Waldo Emerson","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:402"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0404","text":"Are you not ashamed of caring so much for the making of money and for fame and prestige, when you neither think nor care about wisdom and truth and the improvement of your soul?","author":"Socrates","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:403"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0405","text":"In order that all men may be taught to speak the truth, it is necessary that all likewise should learn to hear it","author":"Samuel Johnson","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:404"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0406","text":"Change is the end result of all true learning.","author":"Leo F. Buscaglia","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:405"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0407","text":"Many persons have a wrong idea of what constitutes true happiness. It is not attained through self-gratification but through fidelity to a worthy purpose.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:406"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0408","text":"On the mountains of truth you can never climb in vain: either you will reach a point higher up today, or you will be training your powers so that you will be able to climb higher tomorrow.","author":"Friedrich Nietzsche","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:407"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0409","text":"Learning hath gained most by those books by which the printers have lost.","author":"Thomas Fuller","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:408"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0410","text":"A good book is the precious lifeblood of a master spirit, embalmed and treasured up on purpose to a life beyond life.","author":"John Milton","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:409"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0411","text":"Associate with the noblest people you can find; read the best books; live with the mighty. But learn to be happy alone. Rely upon your energies, and so do not wait for, or depend on other people.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:410"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0412","text":"To limit the press is to insult a nation; to prohibit reading of certain books is to declare the inhabitants to be either fools or slaves","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:411"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0413","text":"Something in human nature causes us to start slacking off at our moment of greatest accomplishment. As you become successful, you will need a great deal of self-discipline not to lose your sense of balance, humility, and commitment.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:412"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0414","text":"Commitment means that it is possible for a man to yield the nerve center of his consent to a purpose or cause, a movement or an ideal, which may be more important to him than whether he lives or dies.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:413"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0415","text":"When work, commitment, and pleasure all become one and you reach that deep well where passion lives, nothing is impossible.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:414"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0416","text":"Every human being has a work to carry on within, duties to perform abroad, influence to exert, which are peculiarly his, and which no conscience but his own can teach.","author":"William Ellery Channing","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:415"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0417","text":"Men make history, and not the other way around. In periods where there is no leadership, society stands still. Progress occurs when courageous, skillful leaders seize the opportunity to change things for the better.","author":"Harry S Truman","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:416"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0418","text":"If I had permitted my failures, or what seemed to me at the time a lack of success, to discourage me I cannot see any way in which I would ever have made progress.","author":"Calvin Coolidge","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:417"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0419","text":"Yes, as my swift days near their goal, tis all that I implore: In life and death a chainless soul, with courage to endure.","author":"Emily Bronte","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:418"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0420","text":"It is from numberless diverse acts of courage and belief that human history is shaped. Each time a man stands up for an ideal, or acts to improve the lot of others, or strikes out against injustice, he sends forth a tiny ripple of hope.","author":"Robert F. Kennedy","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:419"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0421","text":"Most of us, swimming against the tides of trouble the world knows nothing about, need only a bit of praise or encouragement -and we will make the goal.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:420"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0422","text":"One of the things I learned the hard way was that it doesn' t pay to get discouraged. Keeping busy and making optimism a way of life can restore your faith in yourself.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:421"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0423","text":"Sometimes creativity just means the daily work of helping others to see a problem in a different way.","author":"Joseph Badaracco","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:422"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0424","text":"Curiosity is the wick in the candle of learning.","author":"William Arthur Ward","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:423"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0425","text":"The public have an insatiable curiosity to know everything. Except what is worth knowing. Journalism, conscious of this, and having tradesman-like habits, supplies their demands.","author":"Oscar Wilde","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:424"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0426","text":"Change is scientific, progress is ethical; change is indubitable, whereas progress is a matter of controversy.","author":"Bertrand Russell","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:425"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0427","text":"In times of profound change, the learners inherit the earth, while the learned find themselves beautifully equipped to deal with a world that no longer exists.","author":"Al Rogers","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:426"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0428","text":"Without change there is no innovation, creativity, or incentive for improvement. Those who initiate change will have a better opportunity to manage the change that is inevitable.","author":"William Pollard","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:427"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0429","text":"Change does not roll in on the wheels of inevitability, but comes through continuous struggle. And so we must straighten our backs and work for our freedom. A man can't ride you unless your back is bent.","author":"Martin Luther King, Jr","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:428"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0430","text":"In a time of drastic change it is the learners who inherit the future. The learned usually find themselves equipped to live in a world that no longer exists.","author":"Eric Hoffer","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:429"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0431","text":"Our destiny changes with our thought; we shall become what we wish to become, do what we wish to do, when our habitual thought corresponds with our desire.","author":"Orison Sweet Marden","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:430"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0432","text":"People often resist change for reasons that make good sense to them, even if those reasons don't correspond to organizational goals. So it is crucial to recognize, reward, and celebrate accomplishments.","author":"Rosabeth Moss Kanter","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:431"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0433","text":"What starts the process, really, are laughs and slights and snubs when you are a kid. If your anger is deep enough and strong enough, you learn that you can change those attitudes by excellence, personal gut performance.","author":"Richard M. Nixon","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:432"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0434","text":"Few will have the greatness to bend history itself; but each of us can work to change a small portion of events, and in the total of all those acts will be written the history of this generation.","author":"Robert F. Kennedy","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:433"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0435","text":"Because we now have a research group, and we are out there working with lots of universities and are able to continue to hire great people, I'm very optimistic about our future. But, it is a future full of change and surprise.","author":"Bill Gates","source":"Work Focus Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Work Focus","sequence:434"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0436","text":"All major religious traditions carry basically the same message, that is love, compassion and forgiveness ... the important thing is they should be part of our daily lives.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:435"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0437","text":"Flatter me, and I may not believe you. Criticize me, and I may not like you. Ignore me, and I may not forgive you. Encourage me, and I will not forget you. Love me and I may be forced to love you.","author":"William Arthur Ward","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:436"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0438","text":"The winter here's cold and bitter, it's chilled us to the bone. We haven't seen the sun for weeks, too long too far from home. I feel just like I'm sinking, and I claw for solid ground. I'm pulled down by the undertow, I never thought I could feel so low. Oh darkness I feel like letting go. If all of the strength and all of the courage. Come and lift me from this place. I know I could love you much better than this.","author":"Sarah McLachlan","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:437"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0439","text":"Courage is like love; it must have hope to nourish it.","author":"Napoleon Bonaparte","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:438"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0440","text":"Courage is like love; it must have hope for nourishment.","author":"Napoleon Bonaparte","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:439"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0441","text":"Christmas gift suggestions from Oren Arnold: To your enemy, forgiveness. To an opponent, tolerance. To a friend, your heart. To a customer, service. To all, charity. To every child, a good example. To yourself, respect.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:440"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0442","text":"Forgiveness is the final form of love.","author":"Reinhold Niebuhr","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:441"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0443","text":"Marriage is three parts love and seven parts forgiveness of sins.","author":"Lao Tzu","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:442"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0444","text":"Be of good courage, and he shall strengthen your heart, all ye that hope in the Lord (Psalms 31:24).","author":"The Bible","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:443"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0445","text":"To do him any wrong was to beget a kindness from him, for his heart was rich - of such fine mould that if you sowed therein the seed of hate, it blossomed charity.","author":"Alfred, Lord Tennyson","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:444"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0446","text":"Love is an act of endless forgiveness, a tender look which becomes a habit.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:445"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0447","text":"At different states in our lives, the signs of love may vary: dependence, attraction, contentment, worry, loyalty, grief, but at the heart, the source is always the same. Human beings have the rare capacity to connect with each other, against all odds.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:446"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0448","text":"My message is the practice of compassion, love and kindness. Compassion can be put into practice if one recognizes the fact that every human being is a member of humanity and the human family regardless of differences in religion, culture, color and creed. Deep down there is no difference.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:447"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0449","text":"Some people think only intellect counts: knowing how to solve problems, knowing how to get by, knowing how to identify an advantage and seize it. But the functions of intellect are insufficient without courage, love, friendship, compassion and empathy.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:448"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0450","text":"Do everything. Love as much as you can. it may hurt but it helps us grow. Give all you have ... you may be poor but you will be content. Always forgive ... .your heart can not afford not to. Teach what you know and learn what you don't. Stay open to all you can, But most importantly, Dream your dream and then capture it ...","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:449"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0451","text":"Real love, I've learned, is a very, very strong form of forgiveness. I don't think people yearn for love because they hate staying home alone on Saturday night or because they dread going into restaurants alone. People want love because they want their taped-together glasses or the extra pounds to be forgiven. They want someone to look past the surface stuff like bad-hair days, a too-loud laugh or potato chips crunching in their living room couch when anyone sits down.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:450"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0452","text":"Forgiveness is the key to action and freedom.","author":"Hannah Arendt","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:451"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0453","text":"It is above all by the imagination that we achieve perception and compassion and hope.","author":"Ursula K. LeGuin","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:452"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0454","text":"As great scientists have said and as all children know, it is above all by the imagination that we achieve perception, and compassion, and hope.","author":"Ursula K. LeGuin","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:453"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0455","text":"A friend drops their plans when you're in trouble, shares joy in your accomplishments, feels sad when you're in pain. A friend encourages your dreams and offers advice--but when you don't follow it, they still respect and love you.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:454"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0456","text":"A heart in love with beauty never grows old.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:455"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0457","text":"The greatest test of courage on earth is to bear defeat without losing heart.","author":"Robert Green Ingersoll","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:456"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0458","text":"Maybe I could have loved you better. Maybe you should have loved me more. Maybe our hearts were just next in line. Maybe everything breaks sometime.","author":"Jewel Kilcher","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:457"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0459","text":"Everybody can be great because anybody can serve. You don't have to have a college degree to serve. You don't have to make your subject and verb agree to serve. You only need a heart full of grace. A soul generated by love","author":"Martin Luther King, Jr","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:458"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0460","text":"True love is when you have to watch a friend leave, with the knowledge that you might never see him again. But you know he'll be in your mind and heart forever.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:459"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0461","text":"If it is true that there are as many minds as there are heads, then there are as many kinds of love as there are hearts.","author":"Leo Nikolaevich Tolstoy","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:460"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0462","text":"Love bravely, live bravely, be courageous, there's really nothing to lose.","author":"Jewel Kilcher","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:461"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0463","text":"We've got to learn there are going to be hard things in our lifetime, but it's love that gives you the strength. It's being nice to people and having a lot of fun and laughing harder than anything, hopefully every single day of your life.","author":"Drew Barrymore","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:462"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0464","text":"Being deeply loved by someone gives you strength, while loving someone deeply gives you courage.","author":"Lao Tzu","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:463"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0465","text":"One is happy as a result of one's own efforts once one knows the necessary ingredients of happiness simple tastes, a certain degree of courage, selfdenial to a point, love of work, and above all, a clear conscience.","author":"George Sand","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:464"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0466","text":"To love someone deeply gives you strength. Being loved by someone deeply gives you courage.","author":"Lao Tzu","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:465"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0467","text":"We too must endure and persevere in the inquiry, and then courage will not laugh at our faintheartedness in searching for courage; which after all may, very likely, be endurance.","author":"Socrates","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:466"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0468","text":"To persevere, trusting in what hopes he has, is courage in a man.","author":"Euripides","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:467"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0469","text":"If you are lucky enough to find a way of life you love, you have to find the courage to live it.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:468"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0470","text":"Hope, like faith, is nothing if it is not courageous; it is nothing if it is not ridiculous.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:469"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0471","text":"History has demonstrated that the most notable winners usually encountered heartbreaking obstacles before they triumphed. They won because they refused to become discouraged by their defeats.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:470"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0472","text":"It hurts to love someone and not be loved in return, but what is the most painful is to love someone and never find the courage to let the person know how you feel.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:471"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0473","text":"Forgiveness does not change the past, but it does enlarge the future.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:472"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0474","text":"All our lives we search for someone who makes us complete.We choose partners and change partners.We dance the song of heartbreak and hope all the while,wondering if somewhere,somehow there is someone searching for us","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:473"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0475","text":"No matter how far off the pedistol the character fell- they always got a 2nd chance. Forgiveness is one of the greatest gifts the Lord has given us. With it comes understanding.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:474"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0476","text":"Love so easily understands what you can see is the smallest part; you don't need Christmas in your hands when you have Christmas in your heart.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:475"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0477","text":"If there are dreams about a beautiful South Africa, there are also roads that lead to their goal. Two of these roads could be named Goodness and Forgiveness.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:476"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0478","text":"In his younger days a man dreams of possessing the heart of the woman whom he loves; later, the feeling that he possesses the heart of a woman may be enough to make him fall in love with her.","author":"Marcel Proust","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:477"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0479","text":"There is no justification without sanctification, no forgiveness without renewal of life, no real faith from which the fruits of new obedience do not grow.","author":"Martin Luther","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:478"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0480","text":"It is easier to get forgiveness than permission.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:479"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0481","text":"Love knows no limit to its endurance, no end to its trust, no fading of its hope; it can outlast anything. Love still stands when all else has fallen.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:480"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0482","text":"They say a person needs just three things to be truly happy in this world: someone to love, something to do, and something to hope for.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:481"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0483","text":"Compromise is but the sacrifice of one right or good in the hope of retaining another--too often ending in the loss of both.","author":"Tryon Edwards","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:482"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0484","text":"Three grand essentials to happiness in this life are something to do, something to love, and something to hope for.","author":"Joseph Addison","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:483"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0485","text":"And now these three remain: faith, hope and love. But the greatest of these is love (1 Corinthians 13:13).","author":"The Bible","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:484"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0486","text":"Hope deferred maketh the heart sick: but when the desire cometh, it is a tree of life (Proverbs 13:12).","author":"The Bible","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:485"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0487","text":"It makes no difference how deeply seated may be the trouble, how hopeless the outlook how muddled the tangle, how great the mistake. A sufficient realization of love will dissolve it all.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:486"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0488","text":"A very small degree of hope is sufficient to cause the birth of love.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:487"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0489","text":"Today, see if you can stretch your heart and expand your love so that it touches not only those to whom you can give it easily, but also to those who need it so much.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:488"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0490","text":"When my heart can beat no more, I hope I die for a principle, or a belief that I had lives for. I will die before my time, because I feel the shadows depth, so much I wanted to accomplish before Iive reached my death.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:489"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0491","text":"If we don't feel love with our heart, then how come that's where it hurts when someone doesn't love you back?","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:490"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0492","text":"Give away you're troubled heart so you're dreams will all come true. Give away you're troubled heart, find love inside of you.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:491"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0493","text":"You've got to sing sometimes like you don't need the money. Love sometimes like you'll never get hurt. You've got to dance, dance, dance like nobody's watching. It's got to come from the heart if you want it to work.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:492"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0494","text":"No matter how many times I tell you she'll break you heart, or how many times she does it, you'll never give up, Why you ask? ... because you love her.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:493"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0495","text":"May the love hidden deep inside your heart find the love waiting in your dreams. May the laughter that you find in your tomorrow wipe away the pain you find in your yesterdays.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:494"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0496","text":"To love is to risk not being loved in return. To hope is to risk pain. To try is to risk failure, but risk must be taken because the greatest hazard in life is to risk nothing.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:495"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0497","text":"But let us, who are of the day, be sober, putting on the breastplate of faith and love; and for an helmet, the hope of salvation (I Thessalonians 5:8).","author":"The Bible","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:496"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0498","text":"Love means to commit oneself without guarantee, to give oneself completely in the hope that our love will produce love in the loved person. Love is an act of faith, and whoever is of little faith is also of little love.","author":"Erich Fromm","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:497"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0499","text":"All we need is the truth in our hand. Someone to call a friend. Never fear the darkness. All we need is just the sun in the sky. And the hope of a summer to come with the meaning of love.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:498"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0500","text":"Always set high value on spontaneous kindness. He whose inclination prompts him to cultivate your friendship of his own accord will love you more than one whom you have been at pains to attach to you.","author":"Samuel Johnson","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:499"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0501","text":"AlwaysOeset a high value on spontaneous kindness. He whose inclination prompts him to cultivate your friendship of his own accord, will love you more than one whom you have been at pains to attach to you.","author":"Samuel Johnson","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:500"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0502","text":"Love comes to those who still hope even though they've been disappointed, to those who still believe even though they've been betrayed, to those who still love even though they'be been hurt before.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:501"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0503","text":"Above all, we must abolish hope in the heart of man. A calm despair, without angry convulsions, without reproaches to Heaven, is the essence of wisdom.","author":"Alfred Victor Vigny","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:502"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0504","text":"I think that when we look for love courageously, it reveals itself, and we wind up attracting even more love. If one person really wants us, everyone does. But if we're alone, we become even more alone. Life is strange.","author":"Paulo Coelho","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:503"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0505","text":"Love is the only reality and it is not a mere sentiment. It is the ultimate truth that lies at the heart of creation.","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:504"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0506","text":"We cannot tell the exact moment a friendship is formed; as in filling a vessel drop by drop, there is at last a drop which makes it run over; so in a series of kindnesses, there is at last one that makes the heart runover.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:505"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0507","text":"A friend is one to whom you can pour out the contents of your heart, chaff and grain alike. Knowing that the gentlest of hands will take and sift it, keep what is worth keeping and with a breath of kindness, blow the rest away.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:506"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0508","text":"If you are a true friend to someone, make sure you are there for them when they need you, be willing to drop everything for them in a heart beat. Just love them like they deserve.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:507"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0509","text":"Kindness in words creates confidence. Kindness in thinking creates profoundness. Kindness in giving creates love.","author":"Lao Tzu","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:508"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0510","text":"Kindness in giving creates love.","author":"Lao Tze","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:509"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0511","text":"Let us all hope that the dark clouds of racial prejudice will soon pass away, and that in some not too distant tomorrow the radiant stars of love and brotherhood will shine over our great nation with all their scintillating beauty.","author":"Martin Luther King, Jr","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:510"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0512","text":"The rose is a flower of love. The world has acclaimed it for centuries. Pink roses are for love hopeful and expectant. White roses are for love dead or forsaken, but the red roses, ah the red roses are for love triumphant.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:511"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0513","text":"But the mother was marvellous above all, and worthy of honourable memory: for when she saw her seven sons slain within the space of one day, she bore it with a good courage, because of the hope that she had in the Lord.","author":"The Bible","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:512"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0514","text":"We've got to learn hard things in our lifetime, but it's love that gives you the strength. It's being nice to people and having a lot of fun and laughing harder than anything, hopefully every single day of your life.","author":"Drew Barrymore","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:513"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0515","text":"When you put faith, hope and love together, you can raise positive kids in a negative world.","author":"Zig Ziglar","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:514"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0516","text":"Love lives on hope, and dies when hope is dead; it is a flame which sinks for lack of fuel.","author":"Charles Caleb Colton","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:515"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0517","text":"Love and compassion are necessities, not luxuries. Without them humanity cannot survive.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:516"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0518","text":"One loves to possess arms, though they hope never to have occasion for them.","author":"Thomas Jefferson","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:517"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0519","text":"But groundless hope, like unconditional love, is the only kind worth having.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:518"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0520","text":"Take hope from the heart of man, and you make him a beast of prey.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:519"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0521","text":"Kindness in women, not their beauteous looks, shall win my love.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:520"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0522","text":"People are governed with the head; kindness of heart is little use in chess.","author":"Chamfort","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:521"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0523","text":"This is my simple religion. There is no need for temples; no need for complicated philosophy. Our own brain, our own heart is our temple; the philosophy is kindness.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:522"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0524","text":"The kindness I have longest remembered has been of this sort, the sort unsaid; so far behind the speaker's lips that almost it already lay in my heart. It did not have far to go to be communicated.","author":"Henry David Thoreau","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:523"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0525","text":"A tree is known by its fruit; a man by his deeds. A good deed is never lost; he who sows courtesy reaps friendship, and he who plants kindness gathers love.","author":"St. Basil","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:524"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0526","text":"The kindness and affection from the public have carried me through some of the most difficult periods, and always your love and affection have eased the journey.","author":"Proverb","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:525"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0527","text":"The best portion of a good man's life is his little, nameless, unremembered acts of kindness and love.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:526"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0528","text":"When you smiled you had my undivided attention. When you laughed you had my urge to laugh with you. When you cried you had my urge to hold you. When you said you loved me, you had my heart forever.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:527"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0529","text":"When you smiled you had my undevided attention, when you laughed, you had my urge to laugh with you, when you cried you had my urge to hold you, when you said that you loved me you had my heart forever.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:528"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0530","text":"A life without love in it is like a heap of ashes upon a deserted hearth - with the fire dead, the laughter stilled, and the light extinguished.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:529"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0531","text":"Because of deep love, one is courageous. Because of frugality, one is generous. Because of not daring to be ahead of the world, one becomes the leader of the world.","author":"Lao Tzu","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:530"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0532","text":"Love is like playing the piano. First you must learn to play by the rules, then you must forget the rules and play from your heart.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:531"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0533","text":"Keep love in your heart. A life without it is like a sunless garden when the flowers are dead.","author":"Oscar Wilde","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:532"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0534","text":"Life without love is like a tree without blossoms or fruit.","author":"Kahlil Gibran","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:533"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0535","text":"Thank you, God, for this good life and forgive us if we do not love it enough.","author":"Garrison Keillor","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:534"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0536","text":"If you give your life as a wholehearted response to love, then love will wholeheartedly respond to you.","author":"Marianne Williamson","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:535"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0537","text":"I am unjust, but I can strive for justice. My life's unkind, but I can vote for kindness. I, the unloving, say life should be lovely. I, that am blind, cry out against my blindness.","author":"Vachel Lindsay","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:536"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0538","text":"Life is short and we never have enough time for gladdening the hearts of those who travel the way with us. Oh, be swift to love! Make haste to be kind.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:537"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0539","text":"We came together underneath the stars above. What started out as liking soon developed into love. I sense a certain something that, in my heart, felt so true that I knew I waited all my life to fall in love with you.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:538"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0540","text":"Every heart sings a song, incomplete, until another heart whispers back. Those who wish to sing always find a song. At the touch of a lover, everyone becomes a poet.","author":"Plato","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:539"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0541","text":"I think all the boys that write the screaming stuff would write the best love songs ... . because they have the most to hide. The guys that are in the most pain are usually the ones with the biggest hearts.","author":"Tori Amos","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:540"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0542","text":"Young love is a flame; very pretty, often very hot and fierce, but still only light and flickering. The love of the older and disciplined heart is as coals, deep burning, unquenchable.","author":"Henry Ward Beecher","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:541"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0543","text":"Young men's love then lies not truly in their hearts, but in their eyes.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:542"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0544","text":"Hallow the body as a temple to comeliness and sanctify the heart as a sacrifice to love; love recompenses the adorers.","author":"Kahlil Gibran","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:543"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0545","text":"An angel in disguise she was, but somehow you fell for her. Until she broke your heart that day, and left you in the rain, but still I love you.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:544"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0546","text":"Love and magic have a great deal in common. They enrich the soul, delight the heart. And they both take practice.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:545"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0547","text":"Love is a hole in the heart.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:546"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0548","text":"For every love there is a heart somewhere to receive it.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:547"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0549","text":"Paradise was made for tender hearts; hell, for loveless hearts.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:548"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0550","text":"The heart that loves is always young.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:549"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0551","text":"But some emotions don't make a lot of noise. It's hard to hear pride. Caring is real faint - like a heartbeat. And pure love - why, some days it's so quiet, you don't even know it's there.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:550"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0552","text":"When angels visit us, we do not hear the rustle of wings, nor feel the feathery touch of the breast of a dove; but we know their presence by the love they create in our hearts.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:551"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0553","text":"You may not love me today, tomorrow, or ever, but I will love you until it kills me, and, even then, you'll be in my heart.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:552"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0554","text":"You only fall in love once, the rest is merely practice to make sure your heart can take it.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:553"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0555","text":"Love is not something your heart falls into, but something that picks it up and sets it soaring.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:554"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0556","text":"Love is not written on paper, for paper can be erased. Nor is it etched on stone, for stone can be broken. But it is enscribed on a heart and there it shall remian forever.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:555"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0557","text":"May God above send down a dove with wings as sharp as a razor. To spear the heart of any guy who loves a girl, then betrays her.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:556"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0558","text":"We are commanded to love God with all our minds, as well as with all our hearts, and we commit a great sin if we forbid or prevent that cultivation of the mind in others which would enable them to perform this duty.","author":"Angelina Grimke","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:557"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0559","text":"Always keep an open mind and a compassionate heart.","author":"Phil Jackson","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:558"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0560","text":"You can't undo anything you've already done, but you can face up to it. You can tell the truth. You can seek forgiveness. And then let God do the rest.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:559"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0561","text":"( We need) 'leadership that is tough enough to demand a great deal from everyone, and leadership that is tender enough to encourage the heart","author":"Thomas Sergiovanni","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:560"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0562","text":"Cherish your visions; cherish your ideals; cherish the music that stirs in your heart, the beauty that forms in your mind, the loveliness that drapes your purest thoughts, for out of them will grow delightful conditions, all heavenly environment; of these if you but remain true to them, your world will at last be built.","author":"James Allen","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:561"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0563","text":"The harder the conflict, the more glorious the triumph. What we obtain too cheap, we esteem too lightly; it is dearness only that gives everything its value. I love the man that can smile in trouble, that can gather strength from distress and grow brave by reflection. 'Tis the business of little minds to shrink; but he whose heart is firm, and whose conscience approves his conduct, will pursue his principles unto death.","author":"Thomas Paine","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:562"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0564","text":"As I look back on all that's happened, growing up, growing together, changing you, changing me, there were times when we dreamed together. When we laughed and cried together. As I look back on those days I realize how much I truly miss you, and how much I truly love you. The past may be gone forever ... and whatever the future holds, our todays make the memories of tomorrow. So, my lifetime friend, it is with all my heart that I send you my love, hoping that you'll always carry my smile with you, for all we have meant to each other and for whatever the future may hold.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:563"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0565","text":"I saw the Lord always before me. Because he is at my right hand, I will not be shaken. Therefore my heart is glad and my tongue rejoices; my body also will live in hope, because you will not abandon me to the grave, nor will you let your Holy One see decay. You have made known to me the paths of life; you will fill me with joy in your presence (Acts 2:25-28).","author":"The Bible","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:564"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0566","text":"Would you love a man of a broken shell after the passing of a women's soul? Thoughts that I ask others several upon several, still feeling spirits upon spirits with the few moments of love, comfort, unity, & compassion all in a few seconds the holding of each other. The hole that is missing is slowly filled with happiness, joy, good or bad times.","author":"Brian Perkins","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:565"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0567","text":"Love is always patient and kind; it is never jealous, love is never boastful or conceited; it is never rude or selfish; it does not take offense, and is not resentful. Love takes no pleasure in other peopleis sins but delights in the truth; it is always ready to excuse, to trust, to hope, and to endure whatever comes. Love does not come to an end.","author":"The Bible","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:566"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0568","text":"Nothing worth doing is completed in our lifetime; therefore we must be saved by hope. Nothing true or beautiful makes complete sense in any immediate context of history; therefore we must be saved by faith. Nothing we do, however virtuous, can be accomplished alone; therefore, we are saved by love.","author":"Reinhold Niebuhr","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:567"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0569","text":"I love the man that can smile in trouble, that can gather strength from distress, and grow brave by reflection. Tis the business of little minds to shrink, but he whose heart is firm, and whose conscience approves his conduct, will pursue his principles unto death.","author":"Thomas Paine","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:568"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0570","text":"It is from numberless diverse acts of courage and belief that human history is shaped. Each time a man stands up for an ideal, or acts to improve the lot of others, or strikes out against injustice, he sends forth a tiny ripple of hope, and crossing each other from a million different centers of energy and daring, those ripples build a current that can sweep down the mightiest walls of oppression and resistance.","author":"Robert Francis Kenedy","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:569"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0571","text":"As a rock on the seashore he standeth firm, and the dashing of the waves disturbeth him not. He raiseth his head like a tower on a hill, and the arrows of fortune drop at his feet. In the instant of danger, the courage of his heart here, and scorn to fly.","author":"Akhenaton","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:570"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0572","text":"Love anything and your heart will be wrung and possibly broken. If you want to make sure of keeping it intact you must give it to no one, not even an animal. Wrap it carefully round with hobbies and little luxuries; avoid all entanglements. Lock it up save in the casket or coffin of your selfishness. But in that casket--safe, dark, motionless, airless--it will change. It will not be broken; it will become unbreakable, impenetrable, irredeemable. To love is to be vulnerable.","author":"C. S. Lewis","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:571"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0573","text":"Yes, you can be a dreamer and a doer too, if you will remove one word from your vocabulary: impossible.","author":"Robert H. Schuller","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:572"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0574","text":"Live by what you believe so fully that your life blossoms, or else purge the fear-and-guilt producing beliefs from your life. When people believe one thing and do something else, they are inviting misery. If you give yourself the name, play the game. When you believe something you don't follow with your heart, intellect, and body, it hurts. Don't do that to yourself. Live your belief, or let that belief go. If you are not actively living a belief, it's not really your belief, anyway.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:573"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0575","text":"Forgiveness is a funny thing. It warms the heart and cools the sting.","author":"William Arthur Ward","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:574"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0576","text":"Truly loving another means letting go of all expectations. It means full acceptance, even celebration of another's personhood.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:575"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0577","text":"Music does bring people together. It allows us to experience the same emotions. People everywhere are the same in heart and spirit. No matter what language we speak, what color we are, the form of our politics or the expression of our love and our faith, music proves: We are the same.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:576"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0578","text":"'You'll get over it.' It's the cliches that cause the trouble. To lose someone you love is to alter your life forever. You don't get over it because 'it' is the person you loved. The pain stops, there are new people, but the gap never closes. How could it? The articluarness of someone who mattered enough to grieve over is not stopped by anyone but death. The hole in my heart is in the shape of you and no one else can fit it. Why would I want them to?","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:577"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0579","text":"Never let go of hope. One day you will see that it all has finally come together. What you have always wished for has finally come to be. You will look back and laugh at what has passed and you will ask yourself ... 'How did I get through all of that?' Just never let go of hope. Just never quit dreaming. And never let love depart from your life.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:578"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0580","text":"It is true that every day has its own evil, and its good too. But how difficult must life be, especially farther on when the evil of each day increases as far as worldly things go, if it is not strengthened and comforted by faith. And in Christ all worldly things may become better, and, as it were, sanctified. Theo, woe is me if I do not preach the Gospel; if I did not aim at that and possess faith and hope in Christ, it would be bad for me indeed, but no I have some courage.","author":"Vincent Van Gogh","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:579"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0581","text":"Love is patient, love is kind. It does not envy, it does not boast, it is not proud. It is not rude, it is not self-seeking, it is not easily angered, it keeps no record of wrongs. Love does not delight in evil but rejoices with the truth. It always protects, always trusts, always hopes, always perseveres. (1 Corinthians 13:4-7)","author":"The Bible","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:580"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0582","text":"Failure is simply the opportunity to begin again, this time more intelligently.","author":"Henry Ford","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:581"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0583","text":"The Family is the Country of the heart. There is an angel in the Family who, by the mysterious influence of grace, of sweetness, and of love, renders the fulfilment of duties less wearisome, sorrows less bitter. The only pure joys unmixed with sadness","author":"Giuseppe Mazzini","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:582"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0584","text":"If you begin the day with love in your heart, peace in your nerves, and truth in your mind, you not only benefit by their presence but also bring them to others, to your family and friends, and to all those whose destiny draws across your path that day.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:583"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0585","text":"A loving relationship is one in which the loved one is free to be himself -- to laugh with me, but never at me; to cry with me, but never because of me; to love life, to love himself, to love being loved. Such a relationship is based upon freedom and can never grow in a jealous heart.","author":"Leo F. Buscaglia","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:584"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0586","text":"When we honestly ask ourselves which person in our lives means the most us, we often find that it is those who, instead of giving much advise, solutions, or cures, have chosen rather to share our pain and touch our wounds with a gentle and tender hand. The friend who can be silent with us in a moment of despair or confusion, who can stay with us in an hour of grief and bereavement, who can tolerate not knowing, not curing, not healing and face with us the reality of our powerlessness, that is a friend who cares.","author":"Henri Nouwen","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:585"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0587","text":"The friend who can be silent with us in our moments of despair or confusion, who can stay with us in times of grief and breavement, - who can tolerate not knowing, not curing, not healing, and face us with the reality of our powerlessness, that is a friend who cares.","author":"Henri Nouwen","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:586"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0588","text":"Love is like a friendship caught on fire. In the beginning a flame, very pretty, often hot and fierce, but still only light and flickering. As love grows older, our hearts mature and our love becomes as coals, deep-burning and unquenchable.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:587"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0589","text":"It is lack of love for ourselves that inhibits our compassion toward others. If we make friends with ourselves, then there is no obstacle to opening our hearts and minds to others.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:588"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0590","text":"Amazing, isn't it, how some see the basket half empty and others see it half full? Some see life hopeless, some hopeful. Even when things are less than perfect, if you can think of the good, the beautiful, the hopeful, you'll be more than sustained, you'll conquer. Whatever is true ... whatever is right, whatever is pure, whatever is lovely ... think about such things ... put them into practice, and the God of Peace will be with you.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:589"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0591","text":"There is nothing love cannot face; there is no limit to its faith, its hope, its endurance. Love will never come to an end. Prophecies will cease; tongues of ecstasy will fall silent; knowledge will vanish ... there are three things that last forever: faith, hope and love; and the greatest of the three is love.","author":"The Bible","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:590"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0592","text":"I often wonder whether we do not rest our hopes too much upon constitutions, upon laws and upon courts. These are false hopes; believe me, these are false hopes. Liberty lies in the hearts of men and women; when it dies there, no constitution, no law, no court can save it ...","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:591"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0593","text":"An enchanted world is one that speaks to the soul, to the mysterious depths of the heart and imagination where we find value, love, and union with the world around us. As mystics of many religions have taught, that sense of rapturous union can give a sensation of fulfilment that makes life purposeful and vibrant.","author":"Thomas More","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:592"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0594","text":"Be happy. Talk happiness. Happiness calls out responsive gladness in others. There is enough sadness in the world without yours ... never doubt the excellence and permanence of what is yet to be. Join the great company of those who make the barren places of life fruitful with kindness. Your success and happiness lie in you ... the great enduring realities are love and service ... resolve to keep happy and your joy and you shall form an invincible host against difficulties.","author":"Helen Keller","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:593"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0595","text":"Loving is a feeling that brings both joy and pain to my heart. Joy from being with you, being filled with an emotion so deep and tender that no other feeling can compare. Pain from knowing that I'm so in love, that I'm more vulnerable than I've ever been and more suseptable to heartbreak than I want to be.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:594"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0596","text":"Once in your life, whatever he was to the world, he becomes everthing to you. When you look him in the eyes, traveling to the depths of his soul, and you say a million things without a sound, you know that your own life is inevitably consumed within the rythmic beatings for his very heat. I love him for a million reasons. No paper would do it justice. It is a thing not of the mind, but of the heart. A feeling only felt.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:595"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0597","text":"The trouble is that rich people, well-to-do people, very often don't really know who the poor are; and that is why we can forgive them, for knowledge can only lead to love, and love to service. And so, if they are not touched by them, it's because they do not know them.","author":"Mother Teresa of Calcutta","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:596"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0598","text":"To surpress minority thinking and minority expression would tend to freeze society and prevent progress. Now more than ever, we must keep in the forefront of our minds the fact that whenever we take away the liberties of those we hate, we are opening the way to loss of liberty for those we love.","author":"Wendell Phillips","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:597"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0599","text":"I still pray but it's something automatic, and I'm not even sure I still believe in it ... Because I've suffered, and G-d didn't listen to my prayers. because many times in my life I have tried to love with all my heart, and my love has wound up being trampled or betrayed. If G-d is love, he should have cared more about my feelings.","author":"Paulo Coelho","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:598"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0600","text":"I try to talk to you, but I don't know what to say. I am afraid you don't want me to say anything. So I don't. But inside of me there are words waiting to come out. And tell you how I feel - like how I miss you. And how I love you despite my broken heart. And how I need you in my life. And especially how much I want you. But those words my forever stay in my heart - locked inside. Sometimes I wonder if there are words locked inside you too ... but I'll never know.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:599"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0601","text":"In love all the contradiction of existence merge themselves and are lost. Only in love are unity and duality not at variance. Love must be one and two at the same time. Only love is motion and rest in one. Our heart ever changes its place till it finds love, and then it has its rest ... Bondage and liberation are not antagonistic in love. for love is most free and at the same time most bound.","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:600"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0602","text":"I believe all suffering is caused by ignorance. People inflict pain on others in the selfish pursuit of their happiness or satisfaction. Yet true happiness comes from a sense of peace and contentment, which in turn must be achieved through the cultivation of altruism, of love and compassion, and elimination of ignorance, selfishness, and greed.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:601"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0603","text":"Yes, I love him. I love him more than anything else in this world and there is nothing that I would like better than to hold on to him forever. But I know it's not for the best. So know how matter how much my heart is going to break, I've got to let him go so he can know just how much I love him. Maybe if I'm lucky, he'll come back but if not, I can make it through this.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:602"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0604","text":"When you love someone, and you love them with your heart, it never disapears when you are apart. And when you love someone and you've done all you can do, you set them free, and if that love was true ... when you love someone it will all come back to you.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:603"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0605","text":"Nothing you love is lost. Not really. Things, people - they always go away, sooner or later. You can't hold them, any more than you can hold moonlight. But if they've touched you, if they're inside you, then they're still yours. The only things you ever really have are the ones you hold inside your heart.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:604"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0606","text":"I've often thought about how nice it would be to be in love. But I don't believe you can imagine what it's like if you haven't experienced it. Still, I think about it a lot, of course, and I try to imagine what it would be like. But no girl has made my heart beat really fast yet. I haven't even kissed a girl yet.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:605"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0607","text":"Love anything and your heart will be wrung and possibly broken. If you want to make sure of keeping it intact you must give it to no one, not even an animal. Wrap it carefully round with hobbies and little luxuries; avoid all entanglements. Lock it up safe in the casket or coffin of your selfishness. But in that casket--safe, dark, motionless, airless--it will change. It will not be broken; it will become unbreakable, impenetrable, irredeemable.","author":"C. S. Lewis","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:606"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0608","text":"The hardest part about growing up is letting go with what you have been accustomed to and moving on with something that you haven't experienced yet.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:607"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0609","text":"Each of us in our own way can try to spread compassion into peopleis hearts. Western civilizations these days place great importance on filling the human ibraini with knowledge, but no one seems to care about filling the human ihearti with compassion. This is what the real role of religion is.","author":"Dalai Lama","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:608"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0610","text":"Do not keep the alabaster boxes of your love and tenderness sealed up until your friends are dead. Fill their lives with sweetness, speak cheering words while their ears can hear, and while their hearts can be thrilled and made happier by them.","author":"William Congreve","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:609"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0611","text":"In order to transform schools successfully, educators need to navigate the difficult space between letting go of old patterns and grabbing on to new ones","author":"Deal 1990","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:610"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0612","text":"It takes less energy to be free and flowing than locked up in stress ... we learn by releasing and letting go, not by adding on","author":"William Bates Editor","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:611"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0613","text":"Leaders ... appeal to the heart ... with people's deepest, heartfelt hopes. What are these hopes? Humans have a fundamental longing to believe we are successful in what we do - our need to achieve. Educators are typically denied this sense of success. Bombarded with too many state, national, and district standards for students to master ... teachers are often unclear as to what they are supposed to accomplish","author":"Rick Dufor 2004","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:612"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0614","text":"The constant need to move on, and to document progress, in normal schools means that education tends to be cut up into bite sized task.","author":"Guy Claxton in 'Wise -Up'","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:613"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0615","text":"Any intelligent fool can make things bigger, more complex, and more violent. It takes a touch of genius -- and a lot of courage -- to move in the opposite direction.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:614"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0616","text":"First and last, what is demanded of genius is love of truth.","author":"Goethe, Johann Wolfgang von","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:615"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0617","text":"In this world no one rules by love; if you are but amiable, you are no hero; to be powerful, you must be strong, and to have dominion you must have a genius for organizing.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:616"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0618","text":"The most beautiful things in life cannot be seen or even touched. They must be felt with the heart.","author":"Hellen Keller","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:617"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0619","text":"Gravitation is not responsible for people falling in love.","author":"Einstein","source":"Breakup Healing Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Breakup Healing","sequence:618"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0620","text":"Every morning is a fresh beginning. Every day is the world made new. Today is a new day. Today is my world made new. I have lived all my life up to this moment, to come to this day","author":"Dan Custer","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:619"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0621","text":"I believe that there is an ideal hovering over the earth, an ideal of that Paradise which is not the mere outcome of imagination, but the ultimate reality towards which all things are moving. I believe that this vision of Paradise is to be seen in the sunlight, and the green of the earth, in the flowing streams, in the beauty of springtime and the repose of a winter morning. Everywhere in this earth the spirit of Paradise is awake and sending forth its voice.","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:620"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0622","text":"Never count your friends on sunny days for they all will be around, count your friends on the rainy days when the clouds are grey and lightning shakes the ground. It is then you painfully see the type of friend they really are, when Life delivers a sharp blow do they stay and try to heal the scar? The friends you count during this storm are ones to commend, these people stood their ground these people are labeled 'True Friend'. When the rain finally stops and your new day is here, you will be amazed that after a violent storm a rainbow can appear. Be careful not to begin your count, see what friends the rainbow can make, remember, these are not your true friends their loyalty is fake. Keep sight of the friends that remained when the rain poured down, now begin your count of real friends ones you know will always be around.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:621"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0623","text":"I think all students start off with incredible ability and curiosity, and if they're given the opportunity to pursue that, if they're given a chance to see the neat things about the world in terms that they can appreciate and enjoy, that their abilities will be reinforced and that we'll really achieve so much more potential out of the great students we have than we do today.","author":"Bill Gates","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:622"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0624","text":"It is our desires that limit the scope of our self-realization, hinder our extension of consciousness, and give rise to sin, which is the innermost barrier that keeps us apart from our God, setting up disunion and arrogance of exclusiveness. For sin is not one mere action, but it is an attitude of life which takes for granted that our goal is finite, that our self is the ultimate truth, and that we are not all essentially one but exist each for his own separate individual existence.","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:623"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0625","text":"When dreaming, I'm guided through another world, time and time again. At sunrise I fight to stay asleep, 'cause I don't want to leave the comfort of this place, 'cause there's a hunger, a longing to escape, from the life I live when I'm awake.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:624"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0626","text":"Never suppose that in any possible situation or under any circumstances that it is best for you to do a dishonorable thing however slightly so it may appear to you. Encourage all your virtuous dispositions, and exercise them whenever an opportunity arises, being assured that they will gain strength by exercise ... and that exercise will make them habitual.","author":"Thomas Jefferson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:625"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0627","text":"Whatever you think you can do or believe you can do, begin it. Action has magic, grace and power in it.","author":"Goethe, Johann Wolfgang von","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:626"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0628","text":"If I were again beginning my studies, I would follow the advice of Plato and start with mathematics.","author":"Galileo Galilei","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:627"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0629","text":"For age is opportunity no less than youth itself, though in another dress, and as the evening twilight fades away, the sky is filled with stars, invisible by day.","author":"Henry Wadsworth Longfellow","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:628"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0630","text":"People are like stained-glass windows. They sparkle and shine when the sun is out, but when the darkness sets in their true beauty is revealed only if there is a light from within.","author":"Elisabeth Kubler-Ross","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:629"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0631","text":"Beauty is a form of genius--is higher, indeed, than genius, as it needs no explanation. It is of the great facts in the world like sunlight, or springtime, or the reflection in dark water of that silver shell we call the moon.","author":"Oscar Wilde","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:630"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0632","text":"People are like stained glass windows: they sparkle and shine when the sun is out, but when the darkness sets in their true beauty is revealed only if there is a light within.","author":"Elisabeth Kubler-Ross","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:631"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0633","text":"Each man takes care that his neighbor shall not cheat him. But a day comes when he begins to care that he does not cheat his neighbor. Then all goes well -- he has changed his market-cart into a chariot of the sun.","author":"Ralph Waldo Emerson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:632"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0634","text":"Some of us let our dreams die, but others nourish and protect them, nurse them through bad days 'til they bring them to sunshine and light.","author":"Woodrow T. Wilson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:633"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0635","text":"My heart is singing for joy this morning! A miracle has happened! The light of understanding has shone upon my little pupil's mind, and behold, all things are changed!","author":"Anne Sullivan","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:634"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0636","text":"I'm able to get by very well in life, and also with my work, without beloved God. But I, a suffering human being, can not survive without there being something greater than myself, which for me is my whole life- the creative power ... I want to paint men and women with that certain eternal touch- an idea which the sacred halo embodied earlier and which we seek to express today through light and the palpitating movement of our colors ... The love between a couple is expressed by the unity of two complementary colors, by their mixture and contrasts, by the secretive vibrations of similar tones; the intelligence of a forehead is portrayed by using a light tone on a dark background; hope by a star and a man's passion by a vibrant sunset.","author":"Vincent Van Gogh","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:635"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0637","text":"Keep up prayer from the declining of the sun till the darkness of the night and the morning recitation; surely the morning recitation is witnessed. (The Children of Israel 17.78)","author":"Koran","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:636"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0638","text":"A good idea will keep you awake during the morning, but a great idea will keep you awake during the night.","author":"Marilyn Vos Savant","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:637"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0639","text":"Keep on beginning and failing. Each time you fail, start all over again, and you will grow stronger until you have accomplished a purpose - not the one you began with perhaps, but one you'll be glad to remember.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:638"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0640","text":"I watch out my window as the planes take off into space. Oh, that I could fly away and start fresh. But I must realize that fresh starts also come in the pretty wrapped gift called 'tomorrow.'","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:639"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0641","text":"When a day that you happen to know is Wednesday starts off sounding like Sunday, there is something seriously wrong somewhere.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:640"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0642","text":"Enlighten the people generally, and tyranny and oppressions of body and mind will vanish like evil spirits at the dawn of day.","author":"Thomas Jefferson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:641"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0643","text":"Supposing you have tried and failed again and again. You may have a fresh start any moment you choose, for this thing that we call \"Failure\" is not the falling down, but the staying down.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:642"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0644","text":"Faith is the bird that feels the light and sings when the dawn is still dark.","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:643"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0645","text":"Some people are afraid of what they might find if they try to analyze themselves too much, but you have to crawl into your wounds to discover where your fears are. Once the bleeding starts, the cleansing can begin.","author":"Tori Amos","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:644"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0646","text":"The moment we begin to fear the opinions of others and hesitate to tell the truth that is in us and from motives of policy are silent when we should speak, the divine floods of light and life no longer flow into our souls (Exodus 23:20).","author":"The Bible","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:645"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0647","text":"Hope begins in the dark, the stubborn hope that if you just show up and try to do the right thing, the dawn will come. You wait and watch and work: you don't give up.","author":"Anne Lamott","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:646"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0648","text":"The capacity for hope is the most significant fact of life. It provides human beings with a sense of destination and the energy to get started.","author":"Norman Cousins","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:647"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0649","text":"The future starts today, not tomorrow.","author":"Pope John Paul II","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:648"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0650","text":"Knowledge, the object of knowledge and the knower are the three factors which motivate action; the senses, the work and the doer comprise the threefold basis of action.","author":"Bhagavad Gita","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:649"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0651","text":"To business that we love we rise bedtime, and go to't with delight.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:650"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0652","text":"The man who goes alone can start today; but he who travels with another must wait till that other is ready.","author":"Henry David Thoreau","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:651"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0653","text":"Acting allows me to tell a lot of stories, you know start at the beginning, finish at the end, and tell everything in between. Modeling is just an image.","author":"Cameron Diaz","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:652"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0654","text":"The brain is a wonderful organ. It starts working the moment you get up in the morning and does not stop until you get into the office.","author":"Robert Frost","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:653"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0655","text":"What we call the beginning is often the end. And to make an end is to make a beginning. The end is where we start from.","author":"T. S. Eliot","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:654"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0656","text":"The brain is a wonderful organ; it starts working the moment you get up in the morning, and does not stop until you get into the office.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:655"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0657","text":"What is life, when wanting love? Night without a morning; love's the cloudless summer sun, nature gay adorning.","author":"Robert Burton","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:656"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0658","text":"It is time for blacks to begin the shift from a wartime to a peacetime identity, from fighting for opportunity to the seizing of it.","author":"Shelby Steele","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:657"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0659","text":"So never lose an opportunity of urging a practical beginning, however small, for it is wonderful how often in such matters the mustard-seed germinates and roots itself.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:658"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0660","text":"A well ordered society would be one where the State only had a negative action, comparable to that of a rudder: a light pressure at the right moment to counteract the first suggestion of any loss of equilibrium.","author":"Margaret Thatcher","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:659"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0661","text":"In art, truth and reality begin when one no longer understands what one is doing or what one knows, and when there remains an energy that is all the stronger for being constrained, controlled and compressed.","author":"Henri Matisse","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:660"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0662","text":"Poetry begins in delight and ends in wisdom.","author":"Robert Frost","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:661"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0663","text":"Do not anticipate trouble or worry about what may never happen. Keep in the sunlight.","author":"Benjamin Franklin","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:662"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0664","text":"I arise in the morning torn between a desire to improve (or save) the world and a desire to enjoy (or savor) the world. This makes it hard to plan the day","author":"E. B. White","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:663"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0665","text":"Some people are making such thorough plans for rainy days that they aren't enjoying today's sunshine","author":"William Feather","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:664"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0666","text":"Start with the spirit of the rule- bending it to shape best practice. If the system tightens up, go to the letter of the rule and efficiently do what is necessary with as little energy as possible in a way that minimizes impact","author":"Keith Goldhammer","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:665"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0667","text":"We should be taught not to wait for inspiration to start a thing. Action always generates inspiration. Inspiration seldom generates action","author":"Frank Tibolt","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:666"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0668","text":"Nor do I take into account a danger of starting a chain reaction of a scope great enough to destroy part or all of the planetOe But it is not necessary to imagine the earth being destroyed like a nova by a stellar explosion to understand vividly the growing scope of atomic war and to recognize that unless another war is prevented it is likely to ring destruction on a scale never before held possible, and even now hardly conceived, and that little civilization would survive it.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:667"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0669","text":"Among the great men who have philosophized about [the action of the tides], the one who surprised me most is Kepler. He was a person of independent genius, [but he] became interested in the action of the moon on the water, and in other occult phenomena, and similar childishness.","author":"Galileo Galilei","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:668"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0670","text":"Today the majority of South Africans, black and white, recognize that apartheid has no future. It has to be ended by our own decisive mass action in order to build peace and security. The mass campaign of defiance and other actions of our organization and people can only culminate with the establishment of democracy ... . The factors which necessitated the armed struggle still exist today. We have no option but to continue. We express the hope that a climate conducive to a negotiated settlement will be created soon so that there may no longer be the need for the armed struggle.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:669"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0671","text":"So show a little inspiration/ show them a little spark/ show the world a little light when you show it your heart/ we've got two lives--one we're given,/ and the other one we make/ and the world won't stop/ and actions speak louder/ listen to your heart/ and your heart will say/ everything we got, we got the hard way ...","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:670"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0672","text":"Within us all there are wells of thought and dynamos of energy which are not suspected until emergencies arise. Then often times we find that it is comparatively simple to double or triple our former capacities and to amaze ourselves by the results achieved. Quotas, when set up for us by others, are challenges which goad us on to surpass ourselves. The outstanding leaders of every age are those who set up their own quotas and constantly achieve them.","author":"Thomas J. Watson, Sr.","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:671"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0673","text":"Today a young man on Acid realized that all matter is merely energy condensed to a slow vibration. That we are all one conscienceness experiencing itself subjectively. There's no such thing as death. Life is only a dream and we're the imagination of ourselves. Now here's Tom with the weather.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:672"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0674","text":"Yes, I now feel that it was then on that evening of sweet dreams- that the very first dawn of human love burst upon the icy night of my spirit. Since that period I have never seen nor heard your name without a shiver half of delight, half of anxiety. For years your name never passed my lips, while my soul drank in, with a delirious thirst, all that was uttered in my presence respecting you.","author":"Edgar Allan Poe","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:673"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0675","text":"Most of us who turn to any subject we love remember some morning or evening hour when we got on a high stool to reach down an untried volume, or sat with parted lips listening to a new talker, or for very lack of books began to listen to the voices within, as the first traceable beginning of our love.","author":"T. S. Eliot","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:674"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0676","text":"The future does not belong to those who are content with today, apathetic toward common problems and their fellow man alike, timid and fearful in the face of bold projects and new ideas. Rather, it will belong to those who can blend passion, reason and courage in a personal commitment to the great enterprises and ideals of American society.","author":"Robert F. Kennedy","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:675"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0677","text":"We will only understand the miracle of life fully when we allow the unexpected to happen. Every day, G-d gives us the sun-and also one moment in which we have the ability to change everything that makes us unhappy. Every day, we try to pretend that we haven't perceived that moment, that it doesn't exist, that today is the same as yesterday and will be the same as tomorrow.","author":"Paulo Coelho","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:676"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0678","text":"We grow great by dreams. All big men are dreamers. They see things in the soft haze of spring day or in the red fire of a long winter's evening. Some of us let these great dreams die, but others nourish and protect them; nurse them through bad days till they bring them to the sunshine and light which comes always to those who sincerely hope that their dreams will come true.","author":"Woodrow T. Wilson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:677"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0679","text":"The relativity principle in connection with the basic Maxwellian equations demands that the mass should be a direct measure of the energy contained in a body; light transfers mass. With radium there should be a noticeable diminution of mass. The idea is amusing and enticing; but whether the Almighty is laughing at it and is leading me up the garden path - that I cannot know.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:678"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0680","text":"Where the mind is without fear and the head is held high; Where knowledge is free; Where the world has not been broken up into fragments by narrow domestic walls; Where words come out from the depth of truth; Where tireless striving stretches its arms towards perfection; Where the clear stream of reason has not lost its way in the dreary desert sand of dead habit; Where the mind is led forward by thee into ever widening thought and action ... . into that heaven of freedom, my father, let my country awake.","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:679"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0681","text":"When an American says that he loves his country, he means not only that he loves the New England hills, the prairies glistening in the sun, the wide and rising plains, the great mountains, and the sea. He means that he loves an inner air, an inner light in which freedom lives and in which a man can draw a breath of self-respect.","author":"Adlai E. Stevenson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:680"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0682","text":"Beginning today, treat everyone you meet as if they were going to be dead by midnight. Extend to them all the care, kindness, and understanding you can muster, and do it with no thought of any reward. Your life will never be the same again.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:681"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0683","text":"Separated lovers cheat absence by a thousand fancies which have their own reality. They are prevented from seeing one another and they cannot write; nevertheless they find countless mysterious ways of corresponding, by sending each other the song of birds, the scent of flowers, the laughter of children, the light of the sun, the sighing of the wind, and the gleam of the stars --all the beauties of creation.","author":"Victor Hugo","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:682"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0684","text":"The lack of opportunity is ever the excuse of a weak, vacillating mind. Opportunities! Every life is full of them. Every newspaper article is an opportunity. Every client is an opportunity. Every sermon is an opportunity. Every business transaction is an opportunity: an opportunity to be polite, an opportunity to be manly, an opportunity to be honest, an opportunity to make friends.","author":"Orison Sweet Marden","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:683"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0685","text":"May flowers always line your path and sunshine light your day. May songbirds serenade you every step along the way. May a rainbow run beside you in a sky thatis always blue. And may happiness fill your heart each day your whole life through.","author":"Irish Blessings","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:684"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0686","text":"Measure your health by your sympathy with morning and Spring. If there is no response in you to the awakening of nature, if the prospect of an early morning walk does not banish sleep, if the warble of the first bluebird does not thrill you, know that the morning and spring of your life are past.","author":"Henry David Thoreau","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:685"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0687","text":"I will not wish thee riches nor the glow of greatness, but that wherever thou go, some weary heart shall gladden at thy smile, or shadowed life know sunshine for awhile. And so thy path shall be a track of light, like angels' footsteps passing through the night.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:686"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0688","text":"I often wonder: suppose we could begin life over again, knowing what we were doing? Suppose we could use one life, already ended, as a sort of rough draft for another? I think that every one of us would try, more than anything else, not to repeat himself, at the very least he would rearrange his manner of life, he would make sure of rooms like these, with flowers and light ...","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:687"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0689","text":"It's so sad how we can go through life hating people, thinking that they are so different from us. It is only when we see them at their weakest point, seeing their vulnerability, that we start to realize how similar we all actually are to one another, and how hate is really misunderstanding.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:688"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0690","text":"You must be my Lucky Star, 'cause you shine on me wherever you are. I just think of you and I start to glow, and I need your light, and baby you know. Starlight, starbright first star I see tonight. Starlight, starbright make everything all right. Starlight, starbright first star I see tonight. Starlight, starbright yeah. You must be my Lucky Star 'cause you make the darkness seem so far, and when I'm lost you'll be my guide I just turn around and you're by my side.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:689"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0691","text":"To many a man, and sometimes to a youth, there comes the opportunity to choose between honorable competence and tainted wealth. The young man who starts out to be poor and honorable, holds in his hand one of the strongest elements of success.","author":"Orison Sweet Marden","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:690"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0692","text":"My country owes me nothing. It gave me, as it gives every boy and girl, a chance. It gave me schooling, independence of action, opportunity for service and honor. In no other land could a boy from a country village, without inheritance or influential friends, look forward with unbounded hope.","author":"Herbert Hoover","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:691"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0693","text":"Any power must be an enemy of mankind which enslaves the individual by terror and force, whether it arises under the Fascist or the Communist flag. All that is valuable in human society depends upon the opportunity for development accorded to the individual.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:692"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0694","text":"Brute force crushes many plants. Yet the plants rise again. The Pyramids will not last a moment compared with the daisy. And before Buddha or Jesus spoke the nightingale sang, and long after the words of Jesus and Buddha are gone into oblivion the nightingale still will sing. Because it is neither preaching nor commanding nor urging. It is just singing. And in the beginning was not a Word, but a chirrup.","author":"D. H. Lawrence","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:693"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0695","text":"Whatever you do, or dream you can, begin it. Boldness has genius and power and magic in it.","author":"Goethe, Johann Wolfgang von","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:694"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0696","text":"Men of genius are meteors intended to burn to light their century.","author":"Napoleon Bonaparte","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:695"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0697","text":"The dread of evil is a much more forcible principle of human actions than the prospect of good.","author":"John Locke","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:696"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0698","text":"Do not be too timid and squeamish about your actions. All life is an experience.","author":"Ralph Waldo Emerson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:697"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0699","text":"The mark of a good action is that it appears inevitable in retrospect.","author":"Robert Lewis Stevenson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:698"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0700","text":"One of the great attractions of patriotism it fulfills our worst wishes. In the person of our nation we are able, vicariously, to bully and cheat. Bully and cheat, what's more, with a feeling that we are profoundly virtuous.","author":"Aldous Huxley","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:699"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0701","text":"Take time to deliberate; but when the time for action arrives, stop thinking and go in.","author":"Andrew Jackson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:700"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0702","text":"You see, in life, lots of people know what to do, but few people actually do what they know. Knowing is not enough! You must take action.","author":"Anthony Robbins","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:701"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0703","text":"Action may not always bring happiness; but there is no happiness without action.","author":"Benjamin Disraeli","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:702"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0704","text":"To be able to look back upon ones life in satisfaction, is to live twice","author":"Kahlil Gibran","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:703"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0705","text":"Action to be effective must be directed to clearly conceived ends.","author":"Jawaharlal Nehru","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:704"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0706","text":"We should often feel ashamed of our best actions if the world could see all the motives which produced them.","author":"FranAois de la Rochefoucauld","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:705"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0707","text":"Think like a man of action, act like a man of thought.","author":"Henri Bergson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:706"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0708","text":"If you would hit the mark, you must aim a little above it; every arrow that flies feels the attraction of earth.","author":"Henry Wadsworth Longfellow","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:707"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0709","text":"May you live your life as if the maxim of your actions were to become universal law.","author":"Immanuel Kant","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:708"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0710","text":"Vision without action is a daydream. Action without vision is a nightmare.","author":"Japanese proverb","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:709"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0711","text":"Action itself, so long as I am convinced that it is right action, gives me satisfaction.","author":"Jawaharlal Nehru","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:710"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0712","text":"Thinking is easy, acting is difficult, and to put one's thoughts into action is the most difficult thing in the world.","author":"Goethe, Johann Wolfgang von","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:711"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0713","text":"High achievers spot rich opportunities swiftly, make big decisions quickly and move into action immediately. Follow these principles and you can make your dreams come true.","author":"Robert H. Schuller","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:712"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0714","text":"In the arena of human life the honors and rewards fall to those who show their good qualities in action.","author":"Aristotle","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:713"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0715","text":"Our life is composed greatly from dreams, from the unconscious, and they must be brought into connection with action. They must be woven together.","author":"Anais Nin","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:714"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0716","text":"Actions lie louder than words.","author":"Carolyn Wells","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:715"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0717","text":"We cannot live only for ourselves. A thousand fibers connect us with our fellow men; and among those fibers, as sympathetic threads, our actions run as causes, and they come back to us as effects.","author":"Herman Melville","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:716"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0718","text":"Good actions give strength to ourselves and inspire good actions in others.","author":"Plato","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:717"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0719","text":"Action may not bring happiness but there is no happiness without action.","author":"William James","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:718"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0720","text":"Freedom of speech and freedom of action are meaningless without freedom to think. And there is no freedom of thought without doubt.","author":"Bergen Evans","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:719"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0721","text":"The actions of men are the best interpreters of their thoughts.","author":"John Locke","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:720"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0722","text":"The most decisive actions of our life -- I mean those that are most likely to decide the whole course of our future -- are, more often than not, unconsidered.","author":"Andre Gide","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:721"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0723","text":"I have always thought the actions of men the best interpreters of their thoughts.","author":"John Locke","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:722"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0724","text":"For every action there is an equal and opposite government program.","author":"Bob Wells","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:723"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0725","text":"The superior man acts before he speaks, and afterwards speaks according to his action.","author":"Confucius","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:724"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0726","text":"Never mistake motion for action.","author":"Ernest Hemingway","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:725"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0727","text":"There is nothing more frightful than ignorance in action.","author":"Goethe, Johann Wolfgang von","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:726"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0728","text":"Words without actions are the assassins of idealism.","author":"Herbert Hoover","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:727"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0729","text":"There is not any memory with less satisfaction than the memory of some temptation we resisted.","author":"James Branch Cabell","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:728"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0730","text":"A leader or a man of action in a crisis almost always acts subconsciously and then thinks of the reasons for his action.","author":"Jawaharlal Nehru","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:729"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0731","text":"Thought is the seed of action.","author":"Ralph Waldo Emerson","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:730"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0732","text":"Take time to deliberate, but when the time for action has arrived, stop thinking and go in.","author":"Napoleon Bonaparte","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:731"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0733","text":"Most people of action are inclined to fatalism and most of thought believe in providence.","author":"Honore de Balzac","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:732"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0734","text":"Say not that honor is the child of boldness, nor believe thou that the hazard of life alone can pay the price of it: it is not to the action that it is due, but to the manner of performing it.","author":"Akhenaton","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:733"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0735","text":"A lively, disinterested, persistent liking for truth is extraordinarily rare. Action and faith enslave thought, both of them in order not to be troubled or inconvenienced by reflection, criticism or doubt.","author":"Henri FrEdEric Amiel","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:734"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0736","text":"The greatest joy I know is to do a good action by stealth, and have it found by accident.","author":"Charles Lamb","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:735"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0737","text":"Be not too tame neither, but let your own discretion be your tutor: suit the action to the word, the word to the action.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:736"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0738","text":"There are risks and costs to a program of action but they are far less than the long range risks and costs of comfortable inactions.","author":"John Fitzgerald Kennedy","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:737"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0739","text":"A wise man will not leave the right to the mercy of chance, nor wish it to prevail through the power of the majority. There is but little virtue in the action of masses of men.","author":"Henry David Thoreau","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:738"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0740","text":"The man who is completely wise and virtuous has no need of glory, except so far as it disposes and eases his way to action by the greater trust that it procures him.","author":"Plutarch","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:739"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0741","text":"Action without thought is like shooting without aim.","author":"Proverb","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:740"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0742","text":"Our love must not be a thing of words and fine talk. It must be a thing of action and sincerity (1 John 3:18).","author":"The Bible","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:741"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0743","text":"Great leadership does not mean running away from reality. Sometimes the hard truths might just demoralize the company, but at other times sharing difficulties can inspire people to take action that will make the situation better.","author":"John Kotter","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:742"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0744","text":"You can see that, there is no easy walk to freedom anywhere and many of us will have to pass through the valley of the shadow of death again and again before we reach the mountain tops of our desires. Dangers and difficulties have not deterred us in the past, they will not frighten us now. But we must be prepared for them, like men who mean business and who do not waste energy in vain talk and idle action. The way of preparation for action lies in our rooting out all impurity and indiscipline from our organization and making it the bright and shining instrument that will cleave its way to Africa's freedom.","author":"Nelson Mandela","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:743"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0745","text":"Every man of action has a strong dose of egoism, pride, hardness, and cunning. But all those things will be regarded as high qualities if he can make them the means to achieve great ends.","author":"Charles de Gaulle","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:744"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0746","text":"Suit the action to the world, the world to the action, with this special observance, that you overstep not the modesty of nature.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:745"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0747","text":"Action is eloquence.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:746"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0748","text":"It is a sign of contraction of the mind when it is content, or of weariness","author":"Michel de Montaigne","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:747"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0749","text":"Iron rusts from disuse; water loses its purity from stagnation ... even so does inaction sap the vigour of the mind.","author":"Leonardo da Vinci","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:748"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0750","text":"Just as iron rusts from disuse, even so does inaction spoil the intellect.","author":"Leonardo da Vinci","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:749"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0751","text":"A life of reaction is a life of slavery, intellectually and spiritually. One must fight for a life of action, not reaction.","author":"Rita Mae Brown","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:750"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0752","text":"Get action. Seize the moment. Man was never intended to become an oyster.","author":"Theodore Roosevelt","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:751"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0753","text":"Rhetoric is a poor substitute for action, and we have trusted only to rhetoric. If we are really to be a great nation, we must not merely talk; we must act big.","author":"Theodore Roosevelt","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:752"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0754","text":"While we are free to choose our actions, we are not free to choose the consequences of our actions.","author":"Stephen Covey","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:753"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0755","text":"Any business arrangement that is not profitable to the other person will in the end prove unprofitable for you. The bargain that yields mutual satisfaction is the only one that is apt to be repeated.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:754"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0756","text":"Only actions give life strength; only moderation gives it charm.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:755"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0757","text":"We know what a person thinks not when he tells us what he thinks, but by his actions.","author":"Isaac Bashevis Singer","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:756"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0758","text":"I mean really, the human form can be beautiful in so many different ways, i just don't see a need to limit my attraction to that beauty.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:757"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0759","text":"You're more likely to act yourself into feeling than feel yourself into action. So act! Whatever it is you know you should do, do it.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:758"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0760","text":"Vision without action is a dream. Action without vision is simply passing the time. Action with Vision is making a positive difference.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:759"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0761","text":"What should move us to action is human dignity: the inalienable dignity of the oppressed, but also the dignity of each of us. We lose dignity if we tolerate the intolerable.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:760"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0762","text":"Action makes more fortune than caution.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:761"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0763","text":"For me, words are a form of action, capable of influencing change.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:762"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0764","text":"This is my answer to the gap between ideas and action - I will write it out.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:763"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0765","text":"Set your expectations high; find men and women whose integrity and values you respect; get their agreement on a course of action; and give them your ultimate trust.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:764"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0766","text":"A thought which does not result in an action is nothing much, and an action which does not proceed from a thought is nothing at all.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:765"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0767","text":"The only cure for grief is action.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:766"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0768","text":"Between eigtheen and twenty, life is like an exchange where one buys stocks, not with money, but with actions. Most men buy nothing.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:767"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0769","text":"Concern should drive us into action, not into a depression.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:768"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0770","text":"When Daniel gets on stage, and he just sees, like umOean ugly female, he has this reaction to justOescream. And, like I reckon itis heaps funny, cause the crowd thinks itis cute, but they donit know what heis screaming at.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:769"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0771","text":"Unless your heart, your soul, and your whole being are behind every decision you make, the words from your mouth will be empty, and each action will be meaningless. Truth and confidence are the roots of happiness.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:770"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0772","text":"A complacent satisfaction with present knowledge is the chief bar to the pursuit of knowledge.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:771"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0773","text":"The best advisors ... give us, out of themselves, the ardent spirit and desire to act right, and leave us then, even through many blunders, to find out what our own form of right action is","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:772"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0774","text":"The great end of life is not knowledge but action.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:773"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0775","text":"Words divide us, actions unite us.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:774"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0776","text":"Chaotic action is preferable to orderly inaction.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:775"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0777","text":"If a man has talent and can't use it, he's failed. If he uses only half of it, he has partly failed. If he uses the whole of it, he has succeeded, and won a satisfaction and triumph few men ever know.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:776"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0778","text":"In the frank expression of conflicting opinions lies the greatest promise of wisdom in governmental action.","author":"Louis D. Brandeis","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:777"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0779","text":"Life is made up of constant calls to action, and we seldom have time for more than hastily contrived answers.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Morning Energy Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Morning Energy","sequence:778"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0780","text":"People sleep peaceably in their beds at night only because rough men stand ready to do violence on their behalf.","author":"George Orwell","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:779"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0781","text":"Flirting is the gentle art of making a man feel pleased with himself.","author":"Helen Rowland","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:780"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0782","text":"The release of atom power has changed everything except our way of thinking ... the solution to this problem lies in the heart of mankind. If only I had known, I should have become a watchmaker.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:781"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0783","text":"After silence, that which comes nearest to expressing the inexpressible is music.","author":"Aldous Huxley","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:782"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0784","text":"Love is like racing across the frozen tundra on a snowmobile which flips over, trapping you underneath. At night, the ice-weasels come.","author":"Friedrich Nietzsche","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:783"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0785","text":"When you are old and gray and full of sleep, and nodding by the fire, take down this book and slowly read, and dream of the soft look your eyes had once, and of their shadows deep.","author":"William Butler Yeats","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:784"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0786","text":"One of the surest evidences of friendship that one individual can display to another is telling him gently of a fault. If any other can excel it, it is listening to such a disclosure with gratitude, and amending the error.","author":"Edward G. Bulwer-Lytton","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:785"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0787","text":"I go to sleep to dream because you are my dream. Now, that I have you, my life needs no rest.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:786"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0788","text":"The shortest and surest way to live with honor in the world is to be in reality what we would appear to be; all human virtues increase and strengthen themselves by the practice and experience of them.","author":"Socrates","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:787"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0789","text":"When I am travelling in a carriage, or walking after a good meal, or during the night when I cannot sleep; it is on such occasions that ideas flow best and most abundantly.","author":"Woodrow T. Wilson","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:788"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0790","text":"There may be those on earth who dress better or eat better, but those who enjoy the peace of God sleep better.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:789"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0791","text":"The night is my companion ... solitude my guide ... .and I would be the one to hold you down, kiss you so hard, I'll take your breath away ... my body aches to breathe your breath, your words keep me alive.","author":"Sarah McLachlan","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:790"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0792","text":"Don't part with your illusions. When they are gone you may still exist, but you have ceased to live.","author":"Mark Twain","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:791"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0793","text":"Always remember to slow down in life; live, breathe, and learn; take a look around you whenever you have time and never forget everything and every person that has the least place within your heart.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:792"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0794","text":"He was my North, my South, my East and West, My working week and Sunday rest, My noon, my midnight, my talk, my song; I thought that love would last forever: I was wrong.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:793"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0795","text":"Watching a peaceful death of a human being reminds us of a falling star; one of a million lights in a vast sky that flares up for a brief moment only to disappear into the endless night forever.","author":"Elisabeth Kubler-Ross","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:794"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0796","text":"See how nature - trees, flowers, grass - grows in silence; see the stars, the moon and the sun, how they move in silence ... we need silence to be able to touch souls.","author":"Mother Teresa of Calcutta","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:795"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0797","text":"Nature gives to every time and season some beauties of its own; and from morning to night, as from the cradle to the grave, it is but a succession of changes so gentle and easy that we can scarcely mark their progress.","author":"Charles Dickens","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:796"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0798","text":"Gratitude makes sense of our past, brings peace for today, and creates a vision for tomorrow.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:797"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0799","text":"On the Old Course at St. Andrews: This is the origin of the game, golf in its purest form, and it's still played that way on a course seemingly untouched by time. Every time I play here, it reminds me that this is still a game.","author":"Arnold Palmer","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:798"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0800","text":"You will find that silence or very gentle words are the most exquisite revenge for insult.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:799"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0801","text":"The temple of our purest thoughts is silence.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:800"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0802","text":"Please explain why your silence makes more noise than thunder.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:801"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0803","text":"I still need more healthy rest in order to work at my best. My health is the main capital I have and I want to administer it intelligently.","author":"Ernest Hemingway","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:802"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0804","text":"Hardly a competent workman can be found who does not devote a considerable amount of time to studying just how slowly he can work and still convince his employer that he is going at a good pace.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:803"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0805","text":"Blessed is the person who is too busy to worry in the daytime and too sleepy to worry at night.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:804"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0806","text":"I will release you to be creatively crazy and wonderful for these students ... We will do whatever it takes","author":"Lorraine Monro","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:805"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0807","text":"It is time for us to release ourselves from simplistic and ineffective prescriptions; the time to dream is upon us","author":"Carl Glickman","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:806"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0808","text":"Music does not influence research work, but both are nourished by the same sort of longing, and they complement each other in the release they offer.","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:807"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0809","text":"Quiet is the absence of sound. Silence is the presence of silence","author":"Robert Fripp","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:808"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0810","text":"To one bent on age, death will come as a release. I feel this quite strongly now that I have grown old myself and have come to regard death like an old debt, at long last to be discharged. . . .","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:809"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0811","text":"We need a type of theatre which not only releases the feelings, insights and impulses possible within the particular historical field of human relations in which the action takes place, but employs and encourages those thoughts and feelings which help transform the field itself.","author":"Bertolt Brecht","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:810"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0812","text":"In the night we stumble over things and become acutely conscious of their separateness, but the day reveals the unity which embraces them. And the man whose inner vision is bathed in consciousness at once realizes the spiritual unity which reigns over all racial differences, and his mind no longer stumbles over individual facts, accepting them as final. He realizes that peace is an inner harmony and not an outer adjustment, that beauty carries the assurance of our relationship to reality, which waits for its perfection in the response of our love.","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:811"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0813","text":"The aim of life is some way of living, as flexible and gentle as human nature; so that ambition may stoop to kindness, and philosophy to condor and humor. Neither prosperity nor empire nor heaven can be worth winning at the price of a virulent temper, bloody hands, an anguished spirit, and a vain hatred of the rest of the world.","author":"George Santayana","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:812"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0814","text":"I wish I could fall in love, though it only leads to trouble, oh I know it does. Still Iid fool myself and gladly just to feel I was in love, in love. I wish I could feel my heartbeat rise, and gaze into some gentle, warm, excited eyes, and give myself as truly as an arrow flies, in windless skies. Oh, I remember you in the TV light, holding you close to me where we lay. And now I wish I knew some of those softer nights. Whispering quietly, feeling you turn to me. It was only last night in the winter dark, I dreamed of how you loved in all your innocence, and Iive never known a softer, warmer feeling since; or a truer heart. But maybe these dreams are leading me; maybe love is not as gentle as my memory; maybe time and wishful half-remembered fantasies. Or the greatest heart.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:813"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0815","text":"I ask for your support for our brave men fighting tonight halfway around the world, not for territory, not for glory, but that their younger brothers and their sons and your sons can have a chance to grow up in a world of peace and freedom and justice.","author":"Richard M. Nixon","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:814"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0816","text":"A mother is the truest friend we have, when trials, heavy and sudden, fall upon us; when adversity takes the place of prosperity; when friends who rejoice with us in our sunshine, desert us when troubles thicken around us, still will she cling to us, and endeavor by her kind precepts and counsels to dissipate the clouds of darkness, and cause peace to return to our hearts.","author":"Washington Irving","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:815"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0817","text":"The best of us still have our aspirations for the supreme goals of life, which is so often mocked by prosperous people who now control the world. We still believe that the world has a deeper meaning than what is apparent, and that therein the human soul finds its ultimate harmony and peace. We still know that only in spiritual wealth does civilization attain its end, not in a prolific production of materials, and not in the competition of intemperate power with power.","author":"Rabindranath Tagore","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:816"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0818","text":"The night is bright, with a starlit sky, I sit and think, as time passes by. Oh starry night, with a moonlit sky, take me away, and tell me why. Give me a reason, for loveis end, give me a reason, for why I lost a friend. I sit and think, all night long, about the things, that all went wrong. Starlit sky, give me a reason why.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:817"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0819","text":"Civilization is hoped together, brought under a rule, under the semblance of peace by manifold illusion, but Man's life is thought, and he, despite his terror, cannot cease, ravening through century after century ravening, raging and uprooting, that he may come into the desolation of reality.","author":"William Butler Yeats","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:818"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0820","text":"The real questions are the ones that obtrude upon your consciousness whether you like it or not, the ones that make your mind start vibrating like a jackhammer, the ones that you \"come to terms with\" only to discover that they are still there. The real questions refuse to be placated. They barge into your life at the times when it seems most important for them to stay away. They are the questions asked most frequently and answered most inadequately, the ones that reveal their true natures slowly, reluctantly, most often against your will.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:819"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0821","text":"The surest hindrance of success is to have too high a standard of refinement in our own minds, or too high an opinion of the judgment of the public. He who is determined not to be satisfied with anything short of perfection will never do anything to please himself or others.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:820"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0822","text":"We and the cosmos are one. The cosmos is a vast body, of which we are still parts. The sun is a great heart whose tremors run through our smallest veins. The moon is a great gleaming nerve-centre from which we quiver forever. Who knows the power that Saturn has over us or Venus? But it is a vital power, rippling exquisitely through us all the time ... Now all this is literally true, as men knew in the great past and as they will know again","author":"D. H. Lawrence","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:821"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0823","text":"I have never known a concern to make a decided success that did not do good, honest work, and even in these days of fiercest competition, when everything would seem to be a matter of price, there lies still at the root of great business success the very much more important factor of quality. The effect of attention to quality, upon every man in the service, from the president of the concern down to the humblest laborer, cannot be overestimated.","author":"Andrew Carnegie","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:822"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0824","text":"Everyone has their own special gift. In some it is speech, in some, silence. The world has need of small perfections as well as great achievements.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:823"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0825","text":"It isn't the incompetent who destroy an organization. It is those who have achieved something and want to rest upon their achievements who are forever clogging things up.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:824"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0826","text":"Close your eyes and you will see clearly,cease to listen and you will hear truth, be silent and your heart will sing, seek no contacts and you will find union, be still and you will move forward on the tide of spirit, be gentle and you will need no strength, be patient and you will achieve all things, be humble and you will remain entire.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:825"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0827","text":"I don't believe one grows older. I think that what happens early on in life is that at a certain age one stands still and stagnates.","author":"T. S. Eliot","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:826"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0828","text":"For as old age is that period of life most remote from infancy, who does not see that old age in this universal man ought not to be sought in the times nearest his birth, but in those most remote from it?","author":"Blaise Pascal","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:827"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0829","text":"Age is not a particularly interesting subject. Anyone can get old. All you have to do is live long enough.","author":"Groucho Marx","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:828"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0830","text":"Dreams are renewable. No matter what our age or condition, there are still untapped possibilities within us and new beauty waiting to be born.","author":"Dale E. Turner","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:829"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0831","text":"This is the first convention of the space age - where a candidate can promise the moon and mean it.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:830"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0832","text":"Memory moderates prosperity, decreases adversity, controls youth and delights old age.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:831"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0833","text":"I am part of the sea and stars And the winds of the South and North; Of mountains and Moon and Mars, And the ages sent me forth!","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:832"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0834","text":"The biggest disease this day and age is that of people feeling unloved.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:833"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0835","text":"Art is unquestionably one of the purest and highest elements in human happiness. It trains the mind through the eye, and the eye through the mind. As the sun colors flowers, so does art color life.","author":"John Lubbock, Sr.","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:834"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0836","text":"Where the world ceases to be the scene of our personal hopes and wishes, where we face it as free beings admiring, asking and observing, there we enter the realm of Art and Science","author":"Albert Einstein","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:835"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0837","text":"The art of medicine consists of amusing the patient while Nature cures the disease.","author":"Voltaire","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:836"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0838","text":"The art of pleasing consists in being pleased.","author":"William Hazlitt","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:837"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0839","text":"Be slow to fall into friendship, but when thou art in, continue firm and constant.","author":"Socrates","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:838"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0840","text":"For I have sworn thee fair, and thought thee bright, who art as black as hell, as dark as night.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:839"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0841","text":"Blow, blow, thou winter wind, thou art not so unkind as man's ingratitude.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:840"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0842","text":"Sometimes being a friend means mastering the art of timing. There is a time for silence. A time to let go and allow people to hurl themselves into their own destiny. And a time to prepare to pick up the pieces when it is all over.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:841"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0843","text":"For today and its blessings, I owe the world an attitude of gratitude.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:842"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0844","text":"Because power corrupts, society's demands for moral authority and character increase as the importance of the position increases.","author":"John Adams","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:843"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0845","text":"Nothing strengthens authority so much as silence.","author":"Charles de Gaulle","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:844"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0846","text":"There is one order of beauty which seems made to turn heads. It is a beauty like that of kittens, or very small downy ducks making gentle rippling noises with their soft bills, or babies just beginning to toddle.","author":"T. S. Eliot","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:845"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0847","text":"Think of all the beauty still left around you and be happy.","author":"Anne Frank","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:846"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0848","text":"To me, fair friend, you never can be old. For as you were when first your eye I eyed, such seems your beauty still.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:847"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0849","text":"Interestingly, according to modern astronomers, space is finite. This is a very comforting thought -- particularly for people who can never remember where they have left things.","author":"Woody Allen","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:848"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0850","text":"It's really a wonder that I haven't dropped all my ideals, because they seem so absurd and impossible to carry out. Yet I keep them, because in spite of everything I still believe that people are really good at heart.","author":"Anne Frank","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:849"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0851","text":"The aim of every artist is to arrest motion, which is life, by artificial means and hold it fixed so that a hundred years later, when a stranger looks at it, it moves again since it is life.","author":"William Faulkner","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:850"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0852","text":"He who marries for love without money has good nights and sorry days.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:851"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0853","text":"Develop an interest in life as you see it; the people, things, literature, music-the world is so rich, simply throbbing with rich treasures, beautiful souls and interesting people. Forget yourself.","author":"Henry Miller","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:852"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0854","text":"A note of music gains significance from the silence on either side.","author":"Anne Morrow Lindberg","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:853"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0855","text":"The mintage of wisdom is to know that rest is rust, and that real life is in love, laughter, and work.","author":"Elbert Hubbard","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:854"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0856","text":"The wise man always throws himself on the side of his assailants. It is more his interest than it is theirs to find his weak point.","author":"Ralph Waldo Emerson","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:855"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0857","text":"On life's journey faith is nourishment, virtuous deeds are a shelter, wisdom is the light by day and right mindfulness is the protection by night. If a man lives a pure life, nothing can destroy him.","author":"Buddha","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:856"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0858","text":"For life is but a dream whose shapes return, some frequently, some seldom, some by night and some by day.","author":"James Thomson","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:857"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0859","text":"We are such stuff as dreams are made on, and our little life is rounded with a sleep.","author":"William Shakespeare","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:858"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0860","text":"My dreams were all my own; I accounted for them to nobody; they were my refuge when annoyed - my dearest pleasure when free.","author":"Mary Wollstonecraft Shelley","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:859"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0861","text":"Those who dream by night, in the dusty recesses of their minds wake in the day to find that all was vanity; but the dreamers of the day are dangerous men, for they may act their dream with open eyes, and make it possible.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:860"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0862","text":"Only in our dreams are we free. The rest of the time we need wages.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:861"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0863","text":"I just told you my dreams and you made me see that I could walk into the sun and I could still be me and now I can't deny nothing lasts forever.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:862"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0864","text":"For his anger endureth but a moment; in his favour is life: weeping may endure for a night, but joy cometh in the morning (Psalms 30:5).","author":"The Bible","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:863"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0865","text":"Weeping may endure for a night, but joy cometh in the morning. (Psalms 30:5)","author":"The Bible","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:864"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0866","text":"You can swim all day in the Sea of Knowledge and still come out completely dry. Most people do.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:865"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0867","text":"Who knows how long I've loved you, you know I love you still. Will I wait a lonely lifetime? If you want me to I will.","author":"The Beatles","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:866"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0868","text":"You can do what you want, but saving love doesn't bring any interest.","author":"Mae West","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:867"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0869","text":"We need others. We need others to love and we need to be loved by them. There is no doubt that without it, we too, like the infant left alone, would cease to grow, cease to develop, choose madness and even death.","author":"Leo F. Buscaglia","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:868"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0870","text":"Girls bored me, they still do. I love Mickey Mouse more than any woman I've ever known.","author":"Walt Disney","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:869"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0871","text":"Silence is the true friend that never betrays.","author":"Confucius","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:870"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0872","text":"Books are the carriers of civilization. Without books, history is silent, literature dumb, science crippled, thought and speculation at a standstill. They are engines of change, windows on the world, lighthouses erected in the sea of time.","author":"Barbara W. Tuchman","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:871"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0873","text":"For books are not absolutely dead things, but do contain a potency of life in them ; they do preserve as in a vial the purest efficacy and extraction of that living intellect that bred them.","author":"John Milton","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:872"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0874","text":"I still find each day too short for all the thoughts I want to think, all the walks I want to take, all the books I want to read, and all the friends I want to see.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:873"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0875","text":"The nearest way to come at glory, is to do that for conscience which we do for glory.","author":"Benjamin Franklin","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:874"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0876","text":"Great leaders are pragmatists who can deal with difficult realities but still have the optimism and courage to act.","author":"Nitin Nohria","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:875"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0877","text":"One man scorned and covered with scars still strove with his last ounce of courage to reach the unreachable stars; and the world will be better for this.","author":"Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:876"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0878","text":"Any change is resisted because bureaucrats have a vested interest in the chaos in which they exist.","author":"Richard M. Nixon","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:877"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0879","text":"We always overestimate the change that will occur in the next two years and underestimate the change that will occur in the next ten. Don't let yourself be lulled into inaction.","author":"Bill Gates","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:878"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0880","text":"Gratitude bestows reverence, allowing us to encounter everyday epiphanies, those transcendent moments of awe that change forever how we experience life and the world.","author":"John Milton","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:879"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0881","text":"Morality cannot be legislated but behavior can be regulated. Judicial decrees may not change the heart, but they can restrain the heartless.","author":"Martin Luther King, Jr","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:880"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0882","text":"Every people may establish what form of government they please, and change it as they please, the will of the nation being the only thing essential.","author":"Thomas Jefferson","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:881"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0883","text":"People underestimate their capacity for change. There is never a right time to do a difficult thing. A leader's job is to help people have vision of their potential.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:882"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0884","text":"To stand still is to lose, To move is to gain, To change is to grow.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:883"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0885","text":"Nothing's ever really changed. What difference does it make whether it's the Corporate state or the Nation state? In our struggle for freedom we still find ourselves fighting the state.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:884"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0886","text":"It is still an unending source of surprise for me how a few scribbles on a blackboard or on a piece of paper can change the course of human affairs.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:885"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0887","text":"The public interest is best served by the free exchange of ideas.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:886"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0888","text":"Madness takes its toll. Please have exact change.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:887"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0889","text":"Life it seems is a struggle between what we think; what we see. I'm not going to change my ways just to please you or appease you.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:888"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0890","text":"Instill the love of you into all the world, for a good character is what is remembered.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:889"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0891","text":"Character builds slowly, but it can be torn down within incredible swiftness.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:890"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0892","text":"History is made at night. Character is what you are in the dark.","author":"Anonymous","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:891"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0893","text":"You cannot catch a child's spirit by running after it; you must stand still and for love it will soon itself return.","author":"Arthur Miller","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:892"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0894","text":"A child's spirit is like a child, you can never catch it by running after it; you must stand still, and, for love, it will soon itself come back.","author":"Arthur Miller","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:893"],"isProverb":false},{"id":"life-situation-0895","text":"Some choices we live not only once but a thousand times over, remembering them for the rest of our lives.","author":"Richard Bach","source":"Night Calm Pack","tags":["collection:life_packs","category:Night Calm","sequence:894"],"isProverb":false}]}